title: sunshine preserves
directions: Add apple juice to fruit.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to
a boil.
Let set 1/2 hour.
Return to boil for 4 minutes. Pour into shallow trays and set in the sun until thick.
Bring in at sunset.
Put in small canning jars and water bath according to jam directions.

title: lime honey dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly and keep in a cool place. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: mama lee's outlandish oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, granulated sugar, egg, apple butter and milk in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in oats, 1 cup at a time, until well blended.
Spread 1/2 of the dough in bottom of pan.
Spread preserves over dough to 1/4 inch of sides. Mix white morsels in remaining dough.
Drop by spoonfuls over preserves.
Spread evenly.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Center will be soft.
Run spatula around edge of pan to loosen before cooling.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 2 x 1 x 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: venison stew
directions: Combine flour, seasoned salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Shake cubes of meat until well coated.
Melt butter in frying pan over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Don't overcook.
Put meat in a large stew pot.
Add Burgundy wine, beef bouillon and white wine. Bring to a low boil.
Add carrots, celery, onions, garlic, bay leaves, parsley and herbs. Cover and cook 1 hour.
Add potatoes, mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender. Stir in sour cream and 2 teaspoons paprika.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
(My oven takes 45 minutes.)
Delicious hot or cold!

title: coffee cake
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters, then roll in sugar and cinnamon. Layer in angel food pan, greased.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Layer more biscuit pieces until all gone.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and cheese spread. Combine with mayonnaise, garlic salt and seasoned salt. Add crabmeat and spread mixture on English muffins.
Freeze muffins for 10 minutes.
Remove from freezer and broil in oven until bubbly and crisp.
Cut into 1/4 pieces and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix and sift together the 6 dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, pumpkin, oil, and water.
Combine dry and moistened ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool in pans before turning out.

title: jumping bean dip
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Pour mixture in deep dish pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
If doubled, bake 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: sister emma's bene' cookies
directions: Cream egg and
sugar,
add
flour,
butter and vanilla. Add bene' last (be
sure bene' is cool).
Drop by teaspoons on greased floured sheet.
Bake in moderate 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Sprinkle skinless chicken pieces with seasoned salt.
Dredge pieces in mixture of 2 cups flour with seasoned salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Place in Dutch oven with enough margarine to brown.
When brown, remove to plate.
Make roux by adding flour remaining in dredging dish to margarine remaining in Dutch oven. Add additional margarine, if necessary.
Cook to dark reddish brown (almost burnt).
Add a lot of water.
Stir.
Add chicken pieces, onion and celery, then add water to fill Dutch oven.
Boil chicken until it starts to pull from bone.
Remove chicken from bone.
Remove chicken from broth, placing in bowl to cool.
Turn off heat from under broth.
When pieces are cool, debone and return chicken to broth.
Turn heat back on.
Add okra, tomatoes and gumbo file to taste (approximately 1 1/2 pound).
Cook an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice with Tabasco sauce and soy sauce.

title: aunt cate's blueberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and spice; beat together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture (by hand).
Fold in blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a bowl, combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter. In another bowl, combine pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos in blender (you can crush the Oreos any way you want to, but the blender does a great job).
Combine the first and second bowls of mixture.
Put half of the Oreo cookies into the bottom of a dish. Pour mixture over the Oreos and then put the rest of the Oreos on top of the mixture.
Put in icebox.

title: irene's icebox cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, granulated sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and almond.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Roll cookie dough into logs; wrap in wax paper and plastic wrap.
Refrigerate or freeze logs to bake later.
Slice and bake at 375° for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift soda, flour and cocoa together. Add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Stir in coconut, vanilla and nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in three greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Spoon batter into paper lined muffin tins, filling 2/3 full with cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar.
Add egg and salt, beating well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Spoon one heaping teaspoonful of this mixture into center of each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan before serving.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Mix together the ingredients very well.
Store covered in the refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda, zucchini, nuts and raisins.

title: night-before french toast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x
9-inch
pan
with butter.
Arrange bread slices in one layer in pan.
In
a
large bowl, beat eggs with milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour over bread in pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 4 to 36 hours.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Place almond bark in microwave 2 minutes and melt.
Take out and stir; put back 1 minute.
Take out and stir; put morsels in for 2 minutes.
Take out and stir in peanuts; place on waxed paper by teaspoonful.

title: mock oysters
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Add cheese, mushrooms, soup and broccoli.
Use in patty shells or as dip.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and 7-Up; chill. Add drained crushed pineapple, bananas and marshmallows and chill again.
Top with sugar, pineapple juice, flour and egg; cook and cool.
Whip Dream Whip and add to sauce.
Spread on top of salad.

title: nacho dabs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Set aside 6 1/2 dozen whole tortilla chips.
Place chips on cookie sheet and top each with about 1 teaspoon beans, some cheese and a jalapeno pepper ring.
Bake at 400° for 2 to 3 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serve at once.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop shrimp and green onions.
Mix all ingredients together. Serve chilled with your favorite crackers.

title: taco pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls in glass pie dish to form crust.
Brown meat and onions; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and water. Spread meat mixture over dough.
Spread sour cream over meat. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top, then add chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: carmelita bars
directions: Slice cookie dough in 1/4-inch pieces.
Place into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Molding slightly to fit.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until done.
Cool slightly.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, oil and milk.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes in slightly greased muffin tins.

title: fudge
directions: Stir sugar, butter, milk and salt until mixed.
Boil 6 minutes after coming to a rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Be sure to time carefully. Remove from heat.
Add nuts, chocolate bits and vanilla.
Stir until almost cool.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Scramble eggs and cook into a little pancake.
Place on chopping board; cool.
Stir-fry in oil about 2 minutes the peas, cashews and water chestnuts.
Remove.
Add rice to oil.
Saute in wok; add eggs, vegetables and soy sauce to taste. Heat thoroughly.

title: quick pineapple dessert
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Cut pound cake into 3 layers.
Lay first layer down on serving dish.
Place 1/3 of mixture on cake.
Place second layer on pineapple mixture.
Place another 1/3 of mixture on that layer.
Top with remaining layer, then the last of the pineapple mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate cream delight
directions: Melt margarine, add flour and pecans; mix well.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate 7-up cake
directions: Beat about 4 minutes.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated ham steaks
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass dish.
Refrigerate overnight or at room temperature for 5 hours.
Cook on grill.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Use a mixer to combine all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Cover with topping.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: teriyaki strips
directions: Mix ingredients, except meat strips.
Place meat strips on skewers and marinate in sauce for 24 to 48 hours (turning every 6 to 8 hours).
Barbecue until done.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to pkg. directions in two 9 inch round cake pans. When cooled, slice layers in half forming 4 round layers. Combine pineapple, sugar, and corn starch in sauce pan and cook over medium heat until thickened. When cake is thoroughly cooled, place layers on cake plate and put a layer of filling between each layer. Frost with pineapple icing.

title: thomas' scrumptious chicken nuggets
directions: You just take your chicken and kill it.
Cut it, then cut it into little things.
Cook it on 45 hot, then let it cool off.
You know it's ready, because it gets cold.
Put spices on it.
I always eat it when it has spices.
Just eat it with your hand.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Stir soup, milk and pepper until smooth.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes,
onion, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot top with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Saute onions in butter until well done.
Add the following, blending after each addition: crabmeat, breadcrumbs, parsley, garlic and egg.
Cook until mixture is thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add pimento and seasonings.
Stuff crab shells. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: tennessee pork chops
directions: Brown chops and drain.
Mix well the soup and the milk.
In a skillet, place chops, sliced onion and soup mix and sprinkle with sage and pepper.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt, onion and celery as directed on package; drain.
Add rice, soup and cheese.
Pour mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: norwegian pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and the unbeaten egg; mix well until all are combined.
Add baking powder, salt and vanilla and mix.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased pie plate and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour one cake pan.
Dump pineapple in bottom.
Dump pie filling on top; add dry cake mix and nuts.
Cut butter into chunks and lay on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Take off fire and add Rice Krispies.
Mix.
Let cool until cool enough to roll into balls, then roll in coconut.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl or pan and warm in microwave until warm.
Mix in boiled chicken and pour over chips that are laying in the bottom of a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until most liquid appears to be absorbed.

title: sesame salad
directions: Mix cabbage and onions in large bowl.
Add dressing.
Break up noodles in small pieces.
Add almonds, sesame seed and noodles just before serving.

title: my sister's supreme beef casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions; drain. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar and garlic. Simmer 10 minutes. Cook noodles as directed on box and drain. When noodles are tender and are still hot, mix cream cheese and sour cream with them. Grease a 13 x 9 casserole dish. Pour small amounts of meat mixture; layer noodles and then grated cheese. Keep layering until pan is full. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: pig pick'n barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer on stove and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Pour milk into a bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whip until well blended (about one minute).
Add bananas to pudding mixture, reserving just a few for garnish, and stir gently.
Pour mixture into pie shell and spread whipped topping on top of pie.
Garnish with remaining banana slices.

title: terri's taquito casserole
directions: Combine sausage, scrambled eggs and potatoes in a bowl and mix.
Oil casserole dish.
Tear corn tortillas in halves and line bottom of dish.
Add layer of sausage mixture and top with cheese. Repeat layering until ingredients are gone.
Cover and bake 20 to 30 minutes until cheese bubbles, at 350°.

title: tuna sandwich melts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together all ingredients, except buns. Put spread on one half of bun.
Cover with remaining half.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions; cool.
Combine boxes of Jell-O and prepare according to package directions. Chill until slightly firm, then spoon over cake.
Place oranges over this.
Top with whipped cream when serving.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Coat the bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loan pan with cooking spray.
Dust with flour and set aside.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into oblong pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Then mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk; spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add just enough mayonnaise to lightly cover the ingredients.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: three-way salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
Combine with vegetables, eggs and shrimp.
Toss with dressing just before serving. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: hot guacamole ole
directions: Process jalapeno, garlic and avocado in food processor until finely chopped.
Remove 1/4 of avocado mix from processor.
Add lemon juice to avocado in processor.
Process until smooth. In bowl, mix all of avocado mix and remaining ingredients.
Serve as soon as possible with tortilla chips and water!

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Bake in a shallow dish at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes. The longer the dish, the longer the baking time.

title: christmas punch
directions: Prepare orange juice according to directions.
Mix fruit punch, cranberry juice and orange juice in a 6-quart container.
Add ginger ale and sherbet before serving.

title: sweet peach pickles
directions: For 1 gallon of peeled peaches, boil ingredients.
Drop peeled peaches in boiling syrup and let come to a full boil.
Fill jars. Pour hot mixture over and seal.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken breasts with sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow pan.
Cover with mushrooms. Combine soup, sherry and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: old fashioned chicken soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover, boil, reduce to low.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add 2 cups chicken and 1 cup noodles.
Heat and serve.

title: meatballs with sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except cranberry sauce, sugar, lemon juice and chili sauce.
Shape into balls.
Mix the other 4 ingredients together and pour over uncooked meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: philadelphia rice pudding
directions: Mix all together and place in a 3-quart covered saucepan. Bring to a simmer on top of the stove and then place, covered, in a 300° oven.
Bake without disturbing or stirring for 2 hours and 45 minutes.
The pudding will almost caramelize and become a pale golden color.

title: shredded pork barbecue
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, combine first six ingredients, the seasonings, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke, water and pork. Bring to boil. Cover and simmer until pork is tender, about 50 minutes. Remove pork to a 9x13 inch pan. Cover and let stand 30 minutes. Keep sauce warm. Using 2 forks, shred pork. Return to skillet and over medium heat cook until heated through, about 10 minutes.

title: california casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In hot butter in large skillet, saute onion until golden. Remove from heat.
Stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper; toss lightly to mix well.
Layer half the rice mixture in bottom of baking dish, then half of chilies. Sprinkle with half of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: party potatoes
directions: Blend the cream cheese and sour cream in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Mash potatoes thoroughly until smooth.
Add cream cheese mixture and beat well.
Stir in chives.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
At this point potatoes may be covered and put in refrigerator.
One hour before serving, dot with butter and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except garlic, in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Press a wooden pick through garlic clove.
Add to dressing mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: lentil chili
directions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic. Saut for 5 minutes. Stir in the lentils and bulgur wheat. Add the broth, tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes or until lentils are tender. Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: *strawberry cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each is added.
Alternate sifted dry ingredients with the milk.
Add preserves.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Clean and cut into 2-inch pieces fresh rhubarb.
Mix rhubarb with sugar and flour thoroughly.
Add egg and mix again.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with second crust or lattice crust. Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: chocolate heath dessert
directions: Bake and cook cake as directed on box, using 2 layer pans. Split layers into 2 to make 4 cake pieces.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add soda, cocoa and flour.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk and mix again.
Bake at 350°.

title: beef marinade
directions: Grill on kabobs over medium hot coals for 10 to 15 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatball appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 2 and form meat mixture into 40 meatballs using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Brown meatballs lightly in 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil.
Cover; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.

title: mockahlua
directions: In a large pitcher or measuring cup, combine the water, Splenda, coffee crystals and vanilla. Stir until the coffee and Splenda are completely dissolved. Pour the mixture through a funnel into a 1.5 or 2 liter bottle. (A clean 1.5 liter wine bottle works fine, so long as you've saved the cork.) Pour in the vodka. Cork and shake well. Yield: 32 servings of 1 1/2 ounces; a standard "shot."

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease twelve 3-inch by 1 1/4-inch muffin cups.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, and salt.
In another bowl stir together milk, butter, egg, and vanilla until blended.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients; add milk mixture and stir just to combine.
Mash 1/4 cup blueberries and stir into batter with a few quick strokes; stir in remaining blueberries and walnuts.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: *Let stand in hot water a few minutes.

title: empress xi's imperial international retreat coffee - scotch pot de
directions: Combine the pudding mix, sugar, coffee and milk in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken. Pour a little hot mixture into egg yolks and stir quickly to blend. Add to mixture in saucepan and continue cooking until mixture comes to a full boil.
Chill, then whip cream and fold into chilled pudding.
Spoon into souffle cups or a serving dish.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coney sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook over low heat until done, then put on hot dog buns.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mud pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, egg yolks and vanilla until well blended. Fold in cookies and whipped cream. Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or other 2-quart container. Cover and freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Scoop ice into prepared crust. Drizzle with topping.
Garnish with nuts. Return leftovers to freezer.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press thoroughly into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Pour cheese mixture over first mixture and bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven, or until done (lightly browned).

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Chop lemon into quarters and place it into a pot of boiling water.
Let the water boil until the lemon breaks up well.
Now add your Old Bay.
In the same pot, put your cleaned shrimp in. Let them cook about 3 to 4 minutes until they are pink in color. Remove shrimp from water.
Chill in the refrigerator and serve with cocktail sauce.

title: tomato and pepper relish
directions: Cut tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Mix them.
Cover mixture with salt; let stand overnight.
In morning, drain off liquid and add vinegar and sugar.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Pour into clean jars with lids.

title: deviled crab bake
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in flour, mustard and salt. Stir until mixed.
Stir in milk slowly.
Cook 1 minute until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, red pepper and parsley.
Drain crab meat; chop eggs and stir crab, eggs and half of cracker crumbs into sauce.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop into a hot, well oiled skillet by spoonfuls.
Flatten with spoon to form patty.
Brown on both sides.

title: honey french salad dressing
directions: Combine the ingredients; store in jar in the refrigerator.

title: 15 minute beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet or chafing dish, add round steak strips to hot fat; brown quickly.
Add water, undrained mushrooms and soup mix. Blend well; bring to a boil.
Blend flour and sour cream; add to meat mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened (sauce will be thin). Serve over hot, buttered noodles or fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil, then sifted flour.
Mix small amount of flour with fruit and add to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: taco salad for a crowd
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together, except chips.
Add chips, mix and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine margarine and dressing mix.
Cook chicken until tender and then debone.
Butter casserole dish and layer with half the dressing mix.
Add chicken and pour soup mixture over this.
Top with dressing mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, egg and orange peel.
Mix baking soda into sour milk.
Add flour and sour milk alternately to creamed mixture, ending with flour.
Mix in nuts and raisins. Pour into 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
While cake is hot, pour glaze over.

title: coconut bars
directions: Mix with hands and cream.
Spread on pan and pat down.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt butter. Mix butter, mustard, sugar and minced onions together. Slice dinner rolls in half. Take the top of the dinner rolls off. Spread the mixture on the bottom layer of the rolls. Lay the ham on the mixture, then lay the Swiss cheese on the ham. Put the top of the dinner rolls on and spread the mixture on top. Place in the oven until the cheese is melted.

title: bumble bee chili
directions: Mix ground beef and water well before cooking.
Mix all ingredients together and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally, then add 2 slices toasted bread, crumbled, for thickness.

title: mom's potato cakes
directions: Grate potatoes, onion and egg.
Then add flour.
Mix should be like a pancake batter.
If it's not thick enough, add more flour.
Pour oil into frying pan.
Drop batter with large spoon into bottom.
Brown on both sides.

title: red velvet delight
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, food coloring and vanilla.
Sift flour before measuring.
Sift cocoa, salt and flour together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, starting and stopping with flour.
Beat until smooth and creamy. In a separate bowl, mix together soda and vinegar.
Fold into batter.
Pour into two 9-inch pans that have been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: people chow
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients on low heat. Add cereal. Cool well. Pour a little of this mixture into a Ziploc bag and add some powdered sugar. Shake to coat. Lay out on wax paper to cool. Add as little or more of sugar as desired.

title: semur cake
directions: On wax paper, sift together flour, cornstarch and salt.
In large bowl, beat egg yolks slightly.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Continue to beat until mixture is very thick and ivory color.
Add water and vanilla; beat until evenly blended.
At low speed beat in flour mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time, until blended.

title: impossible cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Place all ingredients, except topping, in blender container.
Blend on high speed, stopping blender occasionally to stir, until smooth (about 3 minutes).
(Or beat in a large bowl on high speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl constantly, for 2 minutes.)

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Combine together and add enough milk to make soupy. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: hot pepper spread
directions: Boil vinegar, water, salt and sugar together for 5 minutes. Mix mustard and flour in a large bowl until smooth.
Pour vinegar into mustard and stir.
Add peppers and cook 10 minutes.
Ready to eat or can.
Makes 10 pints.

title: zucchini squash bake
directions: Amount of each ingredient is your choice.
Cook squash until done.
Cook ground beef and drain.
Mix squash, ground beef and tomatoes together in casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with cheese.
Bake in oven at 400° until cheese is melted or brown.
Can also be done with yellow squash.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Cut in butter.
Add milk while you mix. Put flour on pastry board and roll dough out thick. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: california rice
directions: Cook
rice
as	directed, adding to the cooking water 2 bay leaves.
Remove bay leaves after cooking. Saute the onion in butter and add to cooked rice. Add all ingredients and pour in a 13 x 11-inch buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Add
1 cup sharp cheese on top and bake again until melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix until becomes thick.
Add zucchini and stir thoroughly.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt. Mix with other ingredients until smooth.
Add chopped nuts.
bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Empty package chipped beef into food processor.
Chop well into small pieces; take out half of beef.
Lay on separate plate.
Put cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, seasoning and minced onion in with beef in processor.
Blend well until smooth.
Empty onto beef on plate; cover well.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: sweet onions parmesan(microwave)
directions: Peel onions and cut a slice from top of each.
Reserve tops for use in other recipes.
Arrange onions, cut side up, in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top each onion with 1 teaspoon of butter and 1/2 tablespoon of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover casserole and cook at High for 10 to 12 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn after 5 or 6 minutes.

title: yellow cake-instant pudding frosting
directions: Use round cake pans (at least 3).
Follow instructions on box to make cakes.
Mash banana well; add to milk and blend.
Add pudding and blend.
Frost 3 layers.
You can also add coconut or chopped nuts.
Keep in the refrigerator!

title: marcy's carrots
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; microwave on High 15 minutes, stirring halfway through time.
Combine remaining ingredients with cooked carrot mixture.
Put in greased square baking dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch spring-form pan.
In mixing bowl, blend crumbs, sugar and butter. Press into bottom and sides of pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: freezer meat sauce
directions: Saute garlic, peppers and onions in oil.
Brown the chuck. Add rest of ingredients and simmer at least 3 hours.
This freezes very well. Is excellent as "Sloppy Joes" and on spaghetti.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Alternately add flour and milk with vanilla added.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: aloha dip
directions: Mix together macaroons, sugar and sour cream.
Chill several hours to soften macaroon crumbs.
Do not stir again or macaroon crumbs will break into small pieces.

title: buttermilk crescent rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour and beat.
Stir in the rest of the flour.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in a bowl and grease the top of the dough.
Cover; let rise 1 hour. Punch down.
Roll in 2 (12-inch) circles.
Brush with butter.
Cut pie shaped pieces and roll up.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix last 4 ingredients together and layer 1/4 in casserole dish.
Put 1/2 chicken mixture on top of crumbs, another crumb layer, remaining half of chicken mixture and a last layer of crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
This can be frozen for use on one of those nights when it is impossible to cook.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: To cook chicken, put enough water in a pan to cover chicken and bring to a rolling boil.
Put chicken in pan and cover.
Bring back to rolling boil, turn heat off and let pan sit until cool. Place soup, milk and mayonnaise in pan and bring to a boil.
Place cooked chicken in baking dish, sprinkle with pepper and put a ham slice and a cheese slice on each breast.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Form meat into 4 patties.
Slice potatoes, carrots and onions. Place over meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Wrap each serving in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple slices with caramel sauce
directions: Combine butterscotch bits, cinnamon and milk; heat over low fire until thoroughly blended.
Serve in chafing dish over freshly sliced, peeled apple slices.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Add the milk gradually to the dry ingredients.
Cook in a double boiler, stirring almost constantly, about 10 minutes, until the mixture thickens. Gradually add the slightly beaten egg yolks and cook another 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Fold in the coconut.
Cool, without stirring, for about 10 minutes.
Pour into the pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream, if you wish.

title: garden patch carrots
directions: Slice carrots. Place in a saucepan of cold water to cover. Salt to taste.
Bring to boil, cook about 5 minutes or until just tender.
Drain.
Combine with honey and lemon juice.
May be doubled.
Serves 4.

title: kate's rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add boiling water.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Add egg.
Sift salt and flour and stir gradually into sugar mixture.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator.
When ready to use, remove amount desired. Shape into rolls and let rise in a warm place approximately 20 minutes.
(Should remain in refrigerator at least 3 hours.)

title: tucson meat loaf
directions: Mold all ingredients together into a loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peppered corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and margarine.
(Can be done in microwave; cover with plastic wrap.)
Drain and add tomatoes and corn.
Add creamed corn as is.
Refrigerate 8 hours, if possible.
When casserole is at room temperature, bake 2 hours at 325°.
Cover with foil. Serves 12 to 14.

title: buttermilk party biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons very warm water and set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt in bowl and add Crisco.
Add buttermilk to yeast.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Roll to 3/8 to 1/2-inch thick, cut and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tomato green bean soup(prep. time: 30 minutes)
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion and carrots in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in the broth, beans and garlic; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in the tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Yields 9 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins and sugar in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and undrained pineapple.
Chill to partially set.
Put cranberries and orange through grinder.
Fold into gelatin mixture with celery and nuts.
Pour into 8 1/2-cup mold or dish to be served in squares.

title: chocolate cherry pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: pineapple picnic salad
directions: In a large bowl, gradually stir in pineapple into cream cheese.
Stir in pudding mix.
Fold in chunk pineapple and Cool Whip.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: dad's chunky clam chowder
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook celery and onion until onion is tender.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and bone, saving broth.
Melt butter or oleo and add chopped vegetables.
Simmer.
Add tomatoes, soup and broth. Add seasonings, chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Mix well.
Pour into one large or 2 other casserole dishes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: american cheese
directions: In blender, soak gelatin in cold water.
Assemble other ingredients.
Add
boiling water and whiz briefly to dissolve. Add cashews and liquify.
Add remaining ingredients and blend creamy.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix the sugar and corn meal together.
Preheat oven at 350°. Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar mixture.
While still warm, add beaten eggs, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: no bake cookies 1
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in a medium saucepan. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
(You may want to use less oats if mixture gets too thick.)
Mix well and spoon-drop onto waxed paper.
Let cool completely, then eat and enjoy!

title: hot potato salad with vinegar dressing
directions: In small skillet, heat oil over medium heat; add onion slices and bacon bits and saute until onion is translucent.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture starts to boil.
Add potatoes and cook, stirring gently, until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 servings.

title: mom's salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased dish or steamer pan.
Steam
for
hour.	Serve with lemon or tartar sauce.

title: bacon spinach pie
directions: Wash, drain and chop spinach.
(If frozen spinach is used, thaw and squeeze out the water.)
Combine eggs, sugar and seasonings. Stir in milk. Fold in bacon and spinach.
Pour into pie shell. Top with cheese. Bake on bottom shelf of oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: martha washington colonial chocolate(usa)
directions: In a saucepan mix cocoa and cold water into a smooth paste. Stir in 2 cups water, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and blend in the cornstarch dissolved in a little cold milk.
Boil 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and set in a warm place.
Beat until light and foamy the egg and hot water.
Pour half of the egg mixture into a pitcher.
Blend in hot chocolate slowly.
Pour remaining egg mixture over top.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: harvest bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, pumpkin and oatmeal. Beat well. Sift the dry ingredients and add them to the pumpkin mixture. Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Loosen sides and invert pan on dish towel.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: chocolate wacky cake
directions: Cake:
Put all together in bowl.
Hand mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Place in a slow cooker in order given. Simmer on medium for 8 hours and serve on Pepperidge Farm onion rolls.
Save juice to dip on sandwiches.

title: pork and mushrooms
directions: Cut pork in thin strips; brown in margarine.
Add onion, sliced celery, sliced mushrooms and spices.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes.
Add wine and soy sauce.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes. Serve on hot cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple bread(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Sift flour with baking soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar substitute.
Combine egg, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, along with pineapple, stirring just until ingredients are moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Spread evenly in pan and bake 45 minutes or until done.
For easier slicing, store overnight in refrigerator before serving.
Yields 1 loaf (22 slices).

title: bean and ham stew
directions: Saute onion.
Mix everything together in large saucepan, including liquids.
Cook until well heated, about 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Add sugar and vanilla and continue creaming until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients and blend into other mixture. Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Makes about 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin cake and icing
directions: Mix well the sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add pumpkin and oil to first 2 mixtures.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 to 7 minutes.

title: mexican cheese ball
directions: Rinse seeds from chiles.
Use food grinder or blender to grind chiles, cheese and pimiento.
Blend water and onion dip mix.
Add with mayonnaise and butter to cheese mixture.
Add pepper.
Mix well.
Pack into lightly buttered bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and stir into eggs.
Add milk and pumpkin.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted into center comes out clean. Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: To make white sauce, melt butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour; cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Using wire whisk, stir in milk; bring to a boil.
Cook, whisking constantly, 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in dressing mix and white pepper; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray medium skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove half of onion mixture; set aside.
Add mushrooms to onion mixture remaining in skillet and cook about 5 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Combine mushroom mixture, green beans and white sauce in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs with reserved onion mixture; sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, until heated through, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tamale-chili pie
directions: Cut tamales in bite size; combine in 1-quart casserole with beans, chili and onion.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Mix flour and cocoa; blend into creamed mixture.
Add pecans; beat on low speed until well blended.
Chill dough in freezer for 20 minutes; roll into 1-inch balls and mash.
Put a Kiss in the middle and roll back into a ball.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and remove to a wire rack.
Cool completely and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: lazy day chicken
directions: Scatter rice on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pieces of chicken, skin side up, on top of rice.
Combine mushroom soup, water and onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, covered.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: red onion jam
directions: Mix onions, vinegar, juice, sage, and pepper.
Stir in sure-jell and add butter on high heat until it comes to a full, rolling boil.
Add sugar an bring to a rolling boil again for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put into hot jars and seal by turning jars upside down for 5 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Combine peas, chestnuts, onion, pimento and soup.
Mix together the margarine and crackers and sprinkle over the top. Add cheese.
Bake at 400° until top is bubbly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate at least 12 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add remaining ingredients.
Mix and drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375°.

title: chicken and broccoli(low-fat)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Mix margarine and flour together in saucepan.
Cook briefly over medium heat. Blend in chicken broth, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Stir in mushrooms and their liquid.
Season to taste.

title: marinated roast
directions: Mix all ingredients, except roast.
Marinate meat for a day or two in refrigerator, turning several times.
Let meat stand at room temperature for an hour before cooking.
Roast, uncovered, with marinade, in preheated 250° oven for two hours.
Allow roast to rest for 15 minutes.
Slice across grain.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening, brown sugar, white sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into balls; roll in sugar and lightly press with bottom of a glass on greased cookie sheet.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger with onions; drain.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer in this order:
1/2 the beans, 1/4 grated cheese, 1/2 hamburger and 1/4 cheese.
Drizzle with taco sauce and repeat in same order, ending with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Can add on or put on side avocado dip and sour cream.
Use corn chips or nacho chips for dip.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Pour mixture over Jell-O in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Fold in cream cheese.
Add pineapple and let cool.
Mix in whipped cream and nuts.
Can be put in a jello mold and garnished.

title: cheryl's flaky pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening with a fork or pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in water with a fork as lightly as possible.
Form a smooth ball. This will make one 2-crust pie, 2 pastry shells or 12 individual tart shells.

title: microwave fried potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Place in microwave safe casserole dish. Cover potatoes with butter and microwave for 5 minutes. Remove and stir. Place back in microwave covered for 15 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top if desired. For added flavor, add chopped onion.

title: six flavor pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together Crisco, butter, sugar and flavorings.
Add alternately the flour, eggs and milk.
Mix very well and pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook noodles. Drain and rinse.
Brown ground beef and drain well.
When beef is cool, mix with taco seasoning.
Mix all ingredients together, except chips and dressing.
Add chips and dressing, a few minutes before serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Place in casserole dish.
Drain green beans and place on top of ground beef.
Pour tomato soup evenly over green beans.
Cover top with seasoned mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Peel, core and slice thick about 1/4 the cucumbers.
Place in a pan with water and lime.
Let this set overnight.
Drain and wash 3 times in clear water.
Cover with cold water and let set for 4 hours.
Drain again.
Mix 1 cup vinegar, alum and coloring. Add this and enough water to cover cucumbers.
Bring to a simmer and let cook for 2 hours; do not boil.
Pour liquid off.
Mix 2 cups vinegar, 6 cups sugar, red hots and 4 sticks of cinnamon. Bring to a boil and pour over drained cucumbers.
Let set overnight.
Reheat in same juice.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes approximately 8 pints.

title: ham and chicken roll-ups
directions: Cut chicken breast in three strips and roll each strip in 2 slices of shaved ham.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix sour cream and soup (undiluted) and pour over roll-ups.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 250°, remove foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Peel cooked potatoes.
Fry bacon.
Combine dry ingredients with liquid and add to bacon.
Bring to a boil and add onion, pepper and peeled, sliced potatoes.
Leave on low heat until ready to serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples and add above ingredients let set for 20 minutes.

title: jiffy peach cake
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Pour peaches and juice into pan. Top with dry cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees according to box directions.

title: favorite chili
directions: Soften beans or use canned. Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed. Stir once. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 5 to 6 hours. Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring the brown sugar oleo and Karo syrup to a rolling boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Add the soda, cream of tartar and salt. Mix well.
Pour over 7 to 8 quarts popped corn.
Place in 2 buttered cookie sheets and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir a couple of times.
Peanuts may be added.

title: beef and peas
directions: Mix cornstarch with a little water and sugar.
Brown in skillet.
Add frozen peas and serve over hot rice.

title: crustless spinach pie
directions: Thaw and drain the spinach.
Mix together well all of the ingredients together.
Grease a 9x9 inch pan and bake in a 350 oven for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first five ingredients
together
and put in baking dish. Put strips of bacon on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti, rinse and drain well; add margarine, egg and Parmesan cheese; blend well.
Press into a pie plate to make crust.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp in wine for 5 minutes and peel. Sprinkle onion with wine, vinegar and black pepper. Drain macaroni and add shrimp, onion, cucumber and tomato together.
Mix with mayonnaise. You may want to add a little more vinegar to mixture to suit your taste.

title: pork lo mein
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Cook celery, green onion and garlic until tender.
Add pork, mushrooms and carrots.
Stir-fry until pork is tender and pink disappears.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Wash and dry basil.
In a food processor grind nuts to a powder and set aside.
Chop basil in food processor.
When well chopped, add Parmesan cheese and mix.
Add chopped nuts and garlic.
Blend in olive oil by hand.
Garlic and olive oil can be adjusted to taste.
Great on pasta.
Cheese tortellini is my favorite.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Roll each biscuit out, one at a time as thin as possible. Slice sausage about 1-inch thick and spread on rolled out dough. Roll up jelly roll fashion and moisten lapped edges to seal. After this is done, slice the pinwheels about 1/2-inch thick and bake in 400° oven as you would biscuits.
Serve as snacks or appetizers with drinks.
Makes about 50 pinwheels.

title: boston baked beans(4 servings)
directions: Slice bacon into 1/2-inch strips.
Saute bacon, onion and garlic for 5 minutes.
Drain beans.
Combine beans, onion mixture and remaining ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Two hours before serving:
Wash broccoli and separate into small pieces or flowerets.
Slice onion thinly and separate.
Add onion and raisins to broccoli.
Pour dressing mixture over this; cover and refrigerate.
Add bacon and sunflower seeds just before serving.

title: virginia meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Bake mushrooms, bottoms up on pan, for 10 minutes at 350°. Drain water.
Mix sausage, onion and cream cheese together.
Fill mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 10 more minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Slice French bread.
Mix both cheeses and mayonnaise to form a thick spread.
Spread on bread and broil until brown on top.
Serve warm.
Add onion to mixture for variety.

title: apple-nut muffins
directions: Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups. In bowl, beat egg with juice, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, sugars, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in nuts and apple.
Fill prepared muffin cups; sprinkle with sugar 'n cinnamon.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan. Makes 12 muffins.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well with beater.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients, then add eggs, beating after each one.
Add oil, carrots and nuts slowly to mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° in 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flavoring and 2 cups flour; mix.
Cut up fruits, nuts and raisins.
Mix 1 cup flour over fruits, nuts and raisins; mix well.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Heat oven to 325°.
Beat together eggs, oil, sugar, tomatoes, vanilla, lemon juice and rind.
Mix dry ingredients with fork; add nuts and pour into pan. Bake 1 hour or until done.
Make during summer months and freeze some for winter.

title: baked onions
directions: Peel onions and
hollow
out the middle (careful not to go through
the
bottom).
Fill
with
margarine;
generously cover with Cajun seasoning.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Place in a 1-quart glass casserole.
Cover
and
microwave
minutes on High.
Let sit a few minutes, then cook another 5 minutes.
If they are tender, they're
ready.
If still hard, cook a little longer. These are great with grilled meats.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix in apples.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and place in bowl.
Add green peppers and onion. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour beans and toss together.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Makes about 8 servings.

title: beefy noodle dinner
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Stir in parsley, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add noodles; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until noodles are done, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cheese melted on top.

title: best ever fudge
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk.
Heat over medium heat until boiling and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chips and vanilla.
Return to heat until melted.
Pour into 9-inch square greased pan.
Cool until set.

title: strawberry limon punch
directions: Puree strawberries in
blender	or food processor until smooth.
Pour into	large pitcher.	Stir in juice concentrates and grenadine.
Refrigerate.	 Just	before	serving,
pour strawberry mixture into large
punch bowl.	Pour in ginger ale and seltzer.
Add ice
cubes.
Garnish	with
lemon
and
lime slices. Makes 36 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: joy's sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in skillet. Do not drain. Add flour, a few teaspoons at a time, coating sausage, stirring often and scraping bottom.
Add milk and water slowly, stirring often.
Reduce heat and let simmer until thickened.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese, in food processor; process with on/off turns until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Serve pesto over cooked pasta; use as dressing for potato salad.
Mix with rice.
Use in soup or as a topping for vegetables.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash bread
directions: Mix eggs, vegetable oil, sugar and vanilla.
Blend, with a spoon, squash, flour and cinnamon into other ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix together coffee, molasses and soda.
Let stand. In second bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg to molasses mixture and stir.
Mix in molasses mixture with dry ingredients.
Mix all together.
Place dough in refrigerator. Roll out dough on floured board.
Do not roll too thin.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool and frost with a powdered sugar frosting.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese and pour into 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese the last ten minutes.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Layer peaches, then pears, then pineapple, then apples.
Mix juices from fruits.
In a saucepan, mix 1 cup juices, margarine, cornstarch and brown sugar.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken. Take off heat.
Add vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Pour over fruit. Put in oven and cook at 350° until starts to bubble.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
In separate bowl, beat egg, vinegar, mustard and water.
Stir these 4 ingredients into flour mixture.
Cook until boiling.
Take off stove.
Add salad dressing.
Pour over potatoes.

title: pan-fried porterhouse with mushrooms
directions: In a skillet or frying pan, heat 1/2 cup butter.
Add mushrooms.
Saute over medium heat 5 minutes.
Add tarragon and cream.
Simmer over low heat until sauce has thickened slightly.

title: bar-be-bake
directions: Flatten and press canned biscuit dough in muffin cups to outline cups.
Brown ground beef lightly.
Add chopped onions, brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Salt to taste.
Fill cups with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together for about 2 minutes until all ingredients are well blended.
Pour into 5 well-greased and floured mini-loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test doneness with a toothpick.
Remove from pans immediately and cool on cake racks. Slice thinly with serrated knife.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk with soda to bananas.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs slightly in a bowl. Stir in pumpkin, sugar and melted butter.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread in loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool on rack 5 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oil, and
egg together in large bowl.
Do not use mixer.
Use wire whisk or large spoon.
Add nuts, apples, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased tube pan or 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup of the milk as directed on package. Using a large mixing bowl, add remaining milk and the pie filling mix. Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Fold in coconut. Spoon into crust. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight. Makes 8 servings.

title: orange baked pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in shallow baking dish and cover with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 1/2 hour longer.
Baste several times.
Serve with baked potatoes and broccoli.

title: streusel mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and then cut in the melted butter. Store in Modular Mates for "quick" use in fruit crisps and quick breads and coffee cake toppings.
If using butter, store in fridge.

title: holiday cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Spoon into 1/2 cup gift containers.
Cover and chill.
Store 1 week.
Serve with crackers.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Boil carrots in 1-inch of water and salt in a saucepan. Cook 15 minutes or until tender. Drain.	Add butter, sugar and nutmeg. Return to heat and stir until carrots are glazed.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in hot oil until golden brown.
Add onion, pepper and hamburger.
Mix in chili powder and salt, then add tomatoes and water.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is fully cooked.

title: peanut butter ya'll pie
directions: Soften ice cream.
Blend peanut butter in thoroughly.
Line a small pan with plastic wrap.
Fill with dessert and press to corners.
Get out air bubbles.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Lift out block by wrap.
Spread crumbs on a sheet of waxed paper. Place crumbs on with your hands, pressing into sides and top of block.
Chill until firm.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice and stir in crushed pineapple.
Add nuts and blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: riz biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk.
Mix all dry ingredients and shortening together.
Then pour in buttermilk mixture.
Mix with hand.
Place on floured flat surface and knead 20 to 30 strokes.
Roll on flat, floured surface; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet or in a cake pan.
Set in warm place until double in size, about an hour.
Bake in 400° oven.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil
chicken
for
about
1 hour or until tender.
Let chicken
cool and remove from the bone.
Melt Velveeta cheese. Combine
milk,
Ro-Tel
tomatoes and green chilies.
Mix well. Layer
an 8-inch baking dish with Fritos.
Spread chicken over Fritos.
Pour
cheese mixture over chicken and Fritos.
Repeat layers, if
necessary.
Bake in the microwave for 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine eggs with flour, garlic salt and pepper; beat with fork until blended.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat. Dip each piece of chicken into egg mixture; coat well.
Drop pieces one at a time into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown on all sides; remove to paper towel to drain.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of oil.
Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1/3 of chicken broth and chicken pieces together in skillet.
Add pineapple and green peppers; cover and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Blend together cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and remaining chicken broth; mix well and add to meat.
Cook about 15 minutes or until chicken is done and broth is thickened.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Cook together bacon, onions, vinegar, brown sugar and mustard. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add all beans.
Bake in a large casserole dish for 2 hours at 325°.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: sprinkle nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10 inch tube pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add oil, water and eggs.
On low speed beat 30 seconds until moistened.
On medium speed, beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in walnuts and sprinkles.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes until cake tester comes out clean.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Cover apricots with water; let stand 30 minutes.
Drain and dice.
Mix sugar, butter, egg and orange juice.
Sift dry ingredients; add with nuts to sugar and egg mixture.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour on top of chicken.
Crumble 1 package of crackers and dot with 1 stick oleo.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: hana's spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil in pan, add onion and garlic, saute until translucent.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar.*
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes over medium heat.
Then serve over your favorite noodles, or for something different use as a sauce over baked chicken.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all pieces of fruit together in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over fruit.
Mix gently and chill well before serving.

title: fettuccine with sausage and green pepper sauce
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, bring sausage and water to a boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
Continue cooking over medium heat until sausage begins to brown.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Saute until onion and pepper are crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms and basil.
Simmer 15 minutes to blend flavors.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Pour mixture over pineapple in a 9 x 13 glass pan.
Layer 3/4 of crackers and cheese over pineapple.
Pour melted butter over top.
Add the rest of the crackers and cheese to form top layer.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Mix soft ingredients well.
Mold ball and garnish with pecans. Chill until firm.

title: fudge brownie ring cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour batter into generously greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 70 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and drizzle with glaze.

title: crookneck squash
directions: Slice squash long length.
Cover squash inside with butter. Slice onion thin; place over butter.
Salt and pepper to taste. Put squash together with toothpick.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Turn gas grill on low setting; cook 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip "try me"
directions: Let spinach thaw.
Squeeze it dry.
Drain water chestnuts and chop fine.
Chop green onions.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream. Stir in onions and water chestnuts.
Add spinach and mix well. Chill 30 minutes and serve.
Tastes great!

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Melt chocolate in top part of double boiler and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Allow to harden.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Sprinkle shrimp with salt.
Brown onion, green pepper and celery in butter in large skillet.
Blend in flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add sauce and vinegar.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: terry's hot crabmeat dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (moderate).
Butter 3 to 4-cup baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, onion, horseradish, heavy cream and salt and pepper to taste in medium bowl.
Stir in crabmeat.
Spoon into prepared baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes or until hot.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Blend in the pie filling. Cut angel food cake into small bite size pieces.
Blend into mixture.
Chill.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Fold into cheese mixture with pecans. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until ready to serve. Cut in squares.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix and
press in 13 x 9-inch pan or medium size cookie sheet. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Turn oven down to 325 degrees for approximately 25-35 minutes more, or until all bubbly is gone.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cool.
Cut off tops and spoon out potatoes, leaving 1/2-inch.
Put dug out potato in a large bowl; add onions, sour cream, cheese, bacon bits and milk.
Mix with mixer or hand and stuff back into potato hull and bake at 350° for about 5 minutes.
Top with parsley flakes or cheese.

title: black forest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 (9-inch) round cake pans with Pam.
Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions. Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs; whisk in salad oil and sugar, then pumpkin.
Add sifted dry ingredients and pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan (11 x 17 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Stir in 1/3 can of coconut and bake.
When done mix cream of coconut and 1/3 can coconut together.
Punch holes in cake and pour mixture over cake.
Let cool and then mix Cool Whip and remainder of coconut and spread on cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: caramel pie(one very large pie or two small ones)
directions: Mix flour and 1 cup sugar; add milk and egg yolks.
Mix well. Add butter and cook in heavy saucepan, stirring constantly.
When thick, add caramelized sugar to hot custard.
(Caramelize sugar by melting in heavy aluminum pan and stirring until light brown.) Cook until very thick.
Cool and pour into baked pastry shell. Cover with meringue and brown in slow oven.

title: homemade pie crust
directions: In large
mixing
bowl, pour in flour.
Cut in shortening. Begin adding cold water, stirring to form dough.
Form a small ball
(about the size of a baseball).
Drop into pie pan and press out
thinly
to
form
crust.
Use
fingers to form edges.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: heavenly seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions in 2-quart serving bowl.
Spread dressing over onions, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Garnish with bacon bits and additional Cheddar cheese.

title: crustless salmon quiche
directions: Drain and flake salmon. Toss with cheese, flour and onion. Grease pie plate or quiche dish. Spread salmon mix in dish. Beat eggs lightly, then add milk, salt and pepper sauce. Pour over salmon mixture. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean (35 to 40 minutes). Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, nutmeg, salt and sugar.
Bake in casserole. Set pan in water.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: ruggles(cookies)
directions: In large bowl, place water and sprinkle yeast.
Stir to dissolve.
Add flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, eggs and margarine.
Mix well to form a dough.
Cover dough and refrigerate 3 hours or more.

title: heritage chili
directions: Brown meat in a pan over charcoal grill, using mesquite charcoal.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over meat while browning. Add meat to large stock pot.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Simmer on stove until tender.
Add tomatoes and V-8 juice and simmer.
The base is now completed.

title: sour milk cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream together the shortening and sugar, add milk and nuts.
In a separate bowl combine the flour, salt, baking soda and nutmeg, slowly add to the sugar mixture, mix well.
On a greased cookie sheet, drop teaspoonfuls of the mixture 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4 for 12-15 minutes until brown.
Place cookie sheets on racks to cool for 5 minutes, then using a greased spatula, carefully remove the cookies.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: salisbury steak supper
directions: Combine ground beef, cracker crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, egg and milk.
Shape into patties.
Brown in electric skillet.
Add potatoes and green beans.
Make gravy according to package directions.
Pour over ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream sugar and flour with butter or margarine.
Add beaten egg yolks and juice and grated rind of the lemons.
Add the milk and lastly fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for about 30 minutes.
Check at 20 or 25 minutes; egg whites will come to the top and look very dark.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first four ingredients well with hands.
Shape into ball and roll in coconut.
Chill until firm.
Soften about 1 hour before serving with crackers.

title: chicken with cashews and snow peas
directions: Marinate chicken 15 minutes in mixture of next 5 ingredients. Heat oil in uncovered wok at 375°.
Add chicken mixture; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add snow peas and water chestnuts; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add stock and salt; stir-fry until slightly thickened. Stir in cashews; stir immediately.

title: almond brickle sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, butter, egg, baking soda and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in almond brickle bits.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Flatten cookies to 1/4 inch thickness with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 8 to 11 minutes or until edges are very lightly browned.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: peanut blossom
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Shape into balls, roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Press a chocolate candy into each.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and marinate shrimp.
Boil down the marinade.
Pour over shrimp in baking dish.
Top with a few bread crumbs and parsley; dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; broil for 5 minutes.

title: rotel rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic; cook until tender. Add tomatoes and juice; cook about 10 minutes in skillet. Add instant rice, soup and salt. Pour into casserole dish; bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and top with cheese. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook hamburger in large pan, stirring and turning often, until brown in color all over.
Drain off excess grease.
Add other ingredients; mix well and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Will do approximately 150 hot dogs.

title: martha's crab dip
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients; top with soda cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve warm with Pepperidge Farm crackers.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar until smooth. Add flour, sour cream and baking soda. Blend eggs one at a time, until mixed well. Add extract and coconut. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: indian pudding
directions: Slowly add corn meal into hot milk, stirring over low heat until thick (15 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Mix sugar, soda and spices and stir into corn meal mixture.
Thoroughly mix in molasses and cold milk.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Serve warm sprinkled with nutmeg.

title: hush puppies(makes approximately 24)
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, soda, salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper (if desired).
Add onion, pepper and milk.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot grease and cook until golden and done (check one for doneness). These are excellent with fish.
I use homemade cocktail sauce to dip hush puppies and eat.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat and add 3 eggs.
Blend in soda, sour cream and milk.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add to batter.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Prepare 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Spread 1/3 of batter in greased angel food pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Repeat twice.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together and serve over cole slaw.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown onions and celery in fat.
Combine these with crumbs, salt, pepper, sage and seasoning.
Add enough water to moisten. Slit a pocket in each pork chop.
Fill with stuffing.
Fasten edge with wooden picks.
Brown chops in heavy skillet, covered.
Then bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine oats and flour.
Add apple juice concentrate and vegetable oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Add egg, raisins, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until done.
Yields 48 cookies.
One serving equals 3 cookies.

title: tuna salad
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients.
Combine with tuna, eggs and celery.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Serves 50.

title: microwave "tater tot casserole"
directions: Crumble and microwave beef on High for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Tater Tots on top of beef.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg (sifted).
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: whole wheat pineapple muffins
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine until fluffy. Add egg and combine. In a separate bowl, sift dry ingredients together, then add to creamed mixture. Stir in undrained pineapple just until all ingredients are moistened. Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: popovers(yield: 6 popovers)
directions: Grease custard cups or pan with 1/4 teaspoon shortening for each cup.
Place in oven and preheat to 450°.
Put in a 4 cup measuring cup or mixing bowl.
Combine beaten eggs, milk and oil. Add flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat with electric mixer or rotary beater until smooth.
Remove pan from oven.
Fill each 1/2 full.
Return to oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Before removing from oven, prick each popover with a fork to let steam escape.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Place croutons on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish, then cheese.
Mix eggs with other ingredients; pour over croutons; refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: artichokes and mushrooms
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of the butter and saute mushrooms and onion until tender.
In greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, arrange mushrooms, onion and artichokes.
Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice.
Melt remaining butter in skillet.
Brown crumbs, stirring constantly. Sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cover a 14-inch pizza pan with aluminum foil.
Slice cookie dough in 1/8-inch circles.
Arrange slices slightly overlapping in bottom of covered pizza pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring water and butter to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour; beat well until mixture forms a smooth ball, which leaves the pan clean.
Put it immediately into mixing bowl.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Beat until thick and glossy and dough will break from spoon.
Pat in lightly greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Press puff down with spatula (it will be quite large).
Cool.
Mix pudding and milk.
Whip cream cheese with 1/4 cup milk and mix with pudding and milk.
Spread over cooled crust.
Cover with Cool Whip; drizzle with chocolate.

title: crawfish jambalaya in hitachi
directions: Wash rice
and drain.
Place all ingredients in Hitachi rice cooker
with
rice.
Do not add water.
Taste for seasoning.
Add salt
and
red
pepper;
