put Hitachi on cook cycle. After cook cycle
is complete, keep on warm cycle for at least 1/2 hour. Serve with garlic bread and green salad.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses; beat.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Yield:
4 dozen cookies.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour peaches over melted butter, then add flour mixture.
Cover top with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with butter or ice cream.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken until done.
Bone and drain a little of the broth off.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.

title: strawberry iced tea
directions: Put ingredients into a very dry blender; blend until powdered. Store in an airtight container.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons in 1 cup of hot water.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into a lasagna pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: vegetable and cheese casserole
directions: Steam vegetables 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain vegetables and mushrooms very well.
Layer 1/2 broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, mushrooms and cheeses.
Repeat, ending with cheeses.
Drop cream of mushroom or cream of celery soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving to allow cheeses to set.

title: golden carrot soup
directions: Combine vegetables, oil, salt and honey in a 3-quart soup pot. Cover and stew over moderate heat for 15 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Puree in a food mill, blender or processor.
Dissolve milk powder in remaining 1/2 cup water and add to carrot puree along with ginger.
Heat through without boiling.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour. Add sugar and salt. In saucepan, put butter, water and cocoa. Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture. In another bowl, put eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Add to mixture and mix well. Bake in greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fettuccine with clams and zucchini
directions: Wash clams in several changes of cold water, rubbing with a stiff brush.
Put the clams in a pot with 1/2 cup of water.
Cover and cook over high heat.
Stir and remove each clam as it opens. (Overcook and they will be tough.)
When all clams are open and out of the pot, pour the liquid into a bowl gently so sand will be left behind.
Remove the clam meat from shells and keep them moist in the bowl of liquid.
When zucchini has soaked, cut off ends and dice into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: great chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into 3 pieces (I throw away the tips).
Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Put chicken in a casserole dish; pour marinade over chicken.
Marinate for at least 1 hour (I marinate overnight).
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in marinade. Turn wings several times during baking.

title: cherry coke salad(8 servings)
directions: Drain pineapple.
Bring pineapple juice and water to a boil. Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Stir in pie filling and Diet Coke.
Chill until slightly thickened and then fold in pineapple. Chill until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: irresistible blueberry cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and liquid alternately.
Mix well.
Add blueberries (if berries are frozen, lightly dust with 1 tablespoon flour to keep from sinking).
Pour in square cake pan. Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
(Dresses up a basic white cake quickly for company!)

title: oven finished fried chicken
directions: Split broilers in half. Remove neck and backbone.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon Accent, salt and pepper.
Let stand.
Mix milk and pancake mix.
Add to mixture 1/2 teaspoon Accent and egg. Stir. Dip pieces of chicken in batter, then into hot grease (one piece at a time).
Arrange browned pieces in shallow baking pan. Add enough hot water to cover bottom of pan 1/4-inch deep. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: ambrosia
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Fold in all ingredients.
Chill until jelled.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, creamed corn, Wesson oil, eggs, baking soda and jalapeno in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 cornbread mixture into an 8-inch skillet.
Cover mixture with shredded cheese.
Pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cold oven pecan pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating thoroughly.
Add flavorings.
Stir in dampened pecans that have been lightly floured with 1 tablespoon flour.
Turn into tube pan and put into cold oven.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake for 1 hour or until cake springs away from sides of pan.

title: ice cream torte
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Thaw ice cream thoroughly until of liquid consistency.
Prepare the vanilla pudding according to package directions using only 1 1/2 cups of milk.
Blend with an electric mixer.
Add melted ice cream and beat until well blended.
Pour into baked shell.
Chill overnight, until firm.
Top with whipped cream and crushed candy bars.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Put chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch or 11 x 15-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices and cream of chicken soup that has been diluted with 1/2 cup water.
Melt stick of margarine and add to stuffing mix and put on top of mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry-raisin scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch round cake pan.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, eggs and raisins.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
With floured hands, pat half of dough into bottom of greased pan.
Spread dough with jam.
Top with remaining dough. Spread evenly.
Using sharp knife, score dough into 8 wedges. Brush top lightly with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Arrange chicken in a baking pan.
Place onion slices and sliced mushrooms over the chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and sherry with a whisk; spread over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Serve with rice.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and milk, alternating and ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start in cold oven and do not open oven while baking.

title: cheese and fruit salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, cottage cheese and jello.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Let set 4 hours.
Other fruit and jello can be substituted.
Strawberry jello and fresh strawberries, peach jello and fresh peach, etc.

title: cracker barrel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix first three ingredients together. Add melted butter into the batter.
Stir ingredients until soft dough forms.
Turn onto surface that has been dusted with flour. Knead 20 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits.
Place in an ungreased 8 x 8 cake pan.
Flatten slightly and brush with melted butter.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese and onion potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice.
Place on Reynolds Wrap.
Slice onions and place on potatoes.
Put pat of butter on top of each and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fold Reynolds Wrap and cook until done.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake.
No time listed, but try it on 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes, but watch closely.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Let stand to cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and oleo or butter.
Line pan with crumbs (save some for top).

title: fannie's chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat sugar, cocoa, salt and egg yolks together.
Add milk slowly to mixture, then add margarine and vanilla.
Beat slightly to mix together.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes until firm.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Heat undiluted soup.
Mix gelatine with 3 tablespoons water. Combine with soup.
Gradually mix with cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in mold rubbed with mayonnaise or sprayed with Pam.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: real baked ham
directions: Cover the ham with cold water and bring slowly to boil; throw out the water.
Replace with cider to cover ham.
Bring to boil over low heat; keep it barely simmering 20 minutes per pound. Skin it and score fat in a diamond pattern; stud with whole cloves.
Mix the mustard and brown sugar; rub well into ham.
Bake another 10 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Toast bread; cut into cubes.
Place in baking dish.
Heat milk to boiling; pour over bread.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Beat eggs with sweetener, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add apples.
Combine with bread mixture and stir.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add applesauce, then sifted dry ingredients.
Beat smooth and fold in raisins.
Bake in waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve plain or frosted.
This cake will remain moist several days in closely covered container.

title: 7-up baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Boil and cook 1 quart of berries.
While berries are cooking, place nearly a stick of margarine in an 11 x 13-inch dish in a 375° to 400° oven.
Add enough water to berries to see through. Add a touch of cinnamon.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Spread this mixture around on the bottom of the dish with margarine.
Dump cooked berries on top.
Bake until brown.

title: cider vinegar dressing
directions: In a heavy saucepan, whisk together the vinegar, eggs, flour, mustard, salt, pepper and 2 cups water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened, about 6 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and artificial sweetener. Pour into clean jars.
Cover; refrigerate up to 3 months.

title: sour cream nut cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Cream egg yolks, sugar and shortening together.
Add sour cream.
Mix well. Add flour, salt, baking soda and nuts. Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done.
Put in cold oven.
Use large loaf pan.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Blend until smooth.
Pour into vegetable mixture and cook until thickened.

title: swiss venison
directions: Cut venison into slices or cubes.
Put in a baking bag.
Place in a crock-pot.
Add onion and pepper.
Mix steak seasoning with water and pour over meat, onion and pepper.
Close bag with a twist tie and poke several holes in top for steam to escape. Cover with lid and cook on low setting about 6 to 8 hours.
You may serve over rice or noodles.

title: deer steak supreme
directions: Line a deep baking dish with foil.
Put steaks in bottom of pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake in a 375° oven for about 1 hour until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chadwick island sauce
directions: In a 2-quart pan, whisk sugar, flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Whisk in water until smooth.
Whisk in egg yolks and blend.
Add rest of ingredients, except oil; whisk constantly. Cook until thickened (5 minutes).
Do not let boil.
Take off heat and beat in oil.
Store in covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Bake at 450 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: white almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar until white.
Add vinegar and almond; mix.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine eggs (applesauce) oil, vanilla, and zucchini.
Add rest of ingredients.
Batter will be thin.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Blend the pumpkin, eggs and vanilla.
Add sugar, cinnamon, ginger, salt, cloves and allspice.
Mix these ingredients well. Add canned milk and continue to mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread dry cake mix on top evenly. Sprinkle on nuts and melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dilly shrimp salad
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Cut large ones in half.
Shred cabbage. Slice pepper and combine both with shrimp.
Chill.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings for dressing.
Chill.
Add toasted, blanched, slivered almonds and dressing to shrimp mixture.
Toss lightly.
Serve on salad greens. Serves 6.

title: grandma's sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add nuts.
Arrange yams and apples in casserole. Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top; broil lightly.

title: herbed sauce for cold salmon
directions: Mince the fresh herbs and mix with other ingredients.
Chill.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine flour with brown sugar and stir in rest of ingredients.
Cook over heat for about 6 minutes, stirring constantly until thick.

title: ham rolls
directions: Split rolls all at once (do not break apart).
Spread with mixture of first five ingredients both top and bottom layer with ham and cheese.
Put rolls back together and brush mixture on tops. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut apart with sharp knife.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef, onion, garlic; drain.
Stir in marinara sauce and water.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/3 of sauce mixture, half of uncooked lasagna noodles, half of combined Ricotta cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and parsley and half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat ending with sauce mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap; vent.
Microwave at High 10 minutes or until sauce boils.
Microwave at Medium (50% power) 30 to 35 minutes or until pasta is tender, rotating dish half turn after 15 minutes. Uncover; top with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
(Can put together the night before except for cooking and refrigerate.)

title: rhoda ayers' chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over rolled oats; let stand.
Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa plus 1/2 package of chips. Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips and walnuts on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or a little less.

title: chili bravo
directions: In large saucepan, combine chili, vegetable juice and onions. Cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in mixed vegetables. Cover.
Simmer an additional 4 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: vienna steaks
directions: Beat egg well.
Mix with other ingredients, except sour cream. Shape into cakes and cook like hamburgers.
Remove meat to serving dish.
Heat sour cream in same pan and pour over meat. Serve with mushrooms.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix until forms a soft ball.
Pinch off in small pieces.
Mash each down with a fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° until golden brown.

title: crescent dogs
directions: Preheat oven to directions for rolls. Slice hot dogs so that you can insert cheese. Roll the hot dogs into each crescent roll. Cook as directed for the rolls.

title: family favorite fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.

title: venetians
directions: Beat the paste, butter, sugar, egg yolks and almond extract until light and fluffy, 5 minutes.
Beat in flour and salt.
Beat egg whites with electric mixer until stiff peaks form; fold into almond mixture.
Divide 3 ways.
Add food coloring.
Heat in a 350° oven.
Heat preserves; spread over top.
Cover with plastic wrap; press down.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: mexican mess
directions: Mix together cream cheese and dip. Place in plate with lip. Sprinkle with 1/2 package dry taco mix. Layer ingredients, 1 at a time. Sprinkle with shredded cheese, then other 1/2 package of taco mix. Refrigerate. Serve with favorite tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix eggs, sugar, butter, corn syrup, oatmeal and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place in 400° oven for 15 minutes, then lower heat to 350° and continue baking 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix sugar cookie mix as directed on box.
Spread on pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool. Mix cheese and sugar until smooth.
Slice bananas and soak in pineapple juice for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled cookie crust like icing.
Put pineapple and other fruit on and sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: overnight refrigerator pancakes
directions: Combine yeast and water in a bowl; let stand for 5 minutes. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Make a well in the center.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir in yeast.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, orange, apples, pineapple and sugar.
Let stand 2 hours or more.
Mix Jell-O with 2 1/2 cups boiling water. When it begins to gel add the first mixture and chill over night.

title: pecan pie
directions: Use pie crust and place pecans on crust.
Pour mix in pie crust slowly.
Place remainder of pecans in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: smothered pork chops(soulfood)
directions: Rub chops with salt and pepper and sprinkle with half of garlic salt.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Gently coat chops with 1/3 cup of the flour, shaking off excess.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Spread strawberry glaze (1/2 jar) over this, then cut the strawberries into halves.
Place over the glaze.
Spread remaining glaze over the strawberries. Top with whipped cream.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: chicken salad surprise
directions: Place leftover chicken (deboned) in food chopper until finely chopped; add eggs and chop (pickle relish, celery and apple can be chopped in food chopper or by hand); mix together and season with salt and pepper to taste. Moisten with real mayonnaise to desired consistency.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with apples or oranges, bananas or any type of fruit that you eat with your fingers.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the shredded cheese, chicken soup, sour cream, chopped onion, 1/2 cup melted margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in the thawed hash brown potatoes. Turn mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss together cornflakes or potato chips and 1/4 cup melted butter. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until the casserole is golden brown and the potatoes are tender.

title: chew cakes
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. add eggs and beat well. Blend in flour and then add vanilla extract and nuts. Bake in a well greased 13x9 x2 inch pan at 300 degrees for 45 minutes. Cookies will fall. When cool sprinkle with sugar and cut into squares.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Peel, cook and mash potatoes until done.
When hamburger is done, put in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add tomato soup.
Put green beans on top.
Add the egg and salt and pepper to the mashed potatoes.
Put over the beans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well; pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Middle will appear soft, but when done will have crust all over.
Slice when cooled.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer.
Grease and flour tube cake pan. Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Don't open oven door at all while cooking.
Cool on rack.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: In a bowl or bag, combine flour, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add chicken pieces and dredge or shake to coat.
Pour 4 tablespoons butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place chicken in pan, turning pieces once to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued ham in pita pockets
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and saute ham, green pepper and onion until lightly browned.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, chili powder, mustard and pepper; simmer 10 minutes. Meanwhile, warm pita loaves in oven.
Cut pita in half and with fingers, spread pocket open in each half and spoon in ham mixture or fill hamburger buns.

title: tuna-cottage cheese casserole
directions: Mix tuna, cheese and 1/4 cup bread crumbs into beaten eggs. Turn into 1-quart casserole and top with remaining buttered bread crumbs.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until set.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Remove skin and bones.
Place salmon in mixing bowl, breaking up into smaller pieces.
Add egg, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in flour.
Blend in potato flakes, onion and black pepper.
Combine baking powder and reserved 1/4 cup liquid.
Stir into salmon mixture until well combined.
Form mixture into 24 croquettes.
Drop into deep hot oil and fry without crowding for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Garnish with dill and lemon wedges.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend until smooth.
Serve with cut up apple.

title: sweet and easy biscotti
directions: Beat
eggs well; add
oil
and	beat,
then
add
flour gradually.	Grease 6 to
8	Pyrex
custard	cups.
Put
enough mixture in each to fill
cup 1 inch.
Place the cups on cookie sheet and bake in 400°
preheated oven for 40 minutes.
Do not open oven door during baking.
Cool on cake rack completely.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle 2 tablespoons salt over the cucumbers and onions; let set 2 hours.
Mix with sugar and vinegar.
Place in small containers using all the liquid and freeze.

title: leon futrell's clam chowder
directions: Barely cover potatoes and onions with water.
Add bacon grease and cook until tender.

title: pecan coconut cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together the butter, brown sugar and egg; add the oatmeal, coconut and pecans.
Add the flour mixture (a little at a time).
Chill. Roll 1 teaspoon dough into balls.
Roll balls in crushed Rice Krispies or cornflakes (about 1 cup).
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: plucking bread
directions: Lightly grease with oil a Bundt pan.
For each can of biscuits, cut biscuits into quarters and dip in margarine, then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in bottom of Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of nuts.
Add next layer of biscuits, cut into quarters and dipped in margarine, then rolled in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Sprinkle the top with the rest of the nuts and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Brown roast.
Place in heavy duty foil paper.
Sprinkle onion soup on top.
Mix water with soup and pour over all.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: First layer is bean dip.
Second is guacamole.
Mix together the sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning; this is the third layer. Top with cheeses, tomato and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Beat the first 2 ingredients until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 2 hours.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix melted butter, brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, turning until crumbly.
Spread 2/3 on bottom of pan; save rest to put on top.
Beat together sugar, strawberries, lemon juice and egg whites until firm peaks.
Then add 1 cup of whipped cream.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle rest of topping on. Place in the freezer for at least 6 hours.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice mix according to package.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach pita
directions: Thaw spinach and drain to remove most of the liquid.
Add scallions.
Mix in cottage cheese and finely crumbled Feta cheese. Add beaten eggs and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Melt butter.
Place wax paper on counter and set fillo dough out with damp cloth over. Brush bottom of baking pan with butter.
Layer 15 sheets of fillo dough, brushing each with butter.
Carefully spread with spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and layer the other 15 sheets, spreading each with melted butter.
Slice before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: onion parmesan stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems; set mushroom caps aside.
Finely chop stems and set aside.
Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place on medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms caps and saute 5 minutes.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.
Coat skillet with cooking spray; add reserved mushroom stems and green onions.
Saute until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in breadcrumbs, Parmesan and salt; set aside.

title: jim's salmon dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese.
Add salmon.
Add chopped green onions to taste.
Mix and serve with crackers or chips.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Cook and debone 4 chicken breasts.
Preheat pie shells according to directions.
Mix cut up chicken, cooked broccoli, mayonnaise and soup together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in individual pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes. Top with cheese. Cook 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin pie(deep dish)
directions: Mix filling ingredients in top of double boiler and cook over hot water until thick.
Cool slightly, then add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour mixture in pie shell and let cool.

title: no-crust hamburger pie
directions: Combine beef, egg,
garlic salt and onion flakes.
Toss lightly in a large
nonstick pie pan.
Spread the meat mixture to line the bottom and
sides of the pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° for 10
to 12 minutes until browned.
Remove from oven and pour in
tomato
sauce.
Stir together the cheese and seasoning and sprinkle over
the tomato sauce.
Return to oven for an additional 5 to
7 minutes.
To serve, cut into wedges. Makes 6 servings.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: texas style eggs(huevos rancheros)
directions: Fry tortillas in shortening.
Do not overcook.
Put a broken egg on top of each tortilla.
Do not break the yolk.
Put a spoonful of tomato sauce on each.
Put slices of cheese and avocado on each.

title: cherry yum yum(or blueberry)
directions: Blend Dream Whip and milk.
Add in the sugar and vanilla. Blend in cream cheese.
In a separate bowl, crush 1 1/2 packaged graham crackers.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Mix crackers and margarine pressing in the dish for a bottom crust.
Pour half the Dream Whip mixture over crust.
Pour 2 cans pie filling over Dream Whip.
Top with last half of the Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed graham crackers.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix beef, soups and water.
Layer tortilla chips, beef mixture, onion and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 layers. Cool. Split layers.
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture and mix with Cool Whip.
Spread between split layers of sour cream mixture. Frost with Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate. Best when made a couple of days ahead of time.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour half the stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish. Melt margarine and
pour
over mix.
Remove chicken from bones and tear in
small
pieces.
Combine soups, chicken and broth. Pour over mix
and margarine.
sprinkle other half of mix over the top. Bake
at
about
minutes
or
until starts bubbling and brown on top.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Place all fruit in strainer and drain at least 2 hours.
Mix with coconut and sour cream.
Allow to sit in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Can be molded; use nonstick spray.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs; add	sugar.	Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Add to
mixture.
Add
melted
Crisco, vanilla and coconut or nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 24 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots with squash and onion mixture.
Melt butter.
Stir in stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 stuffing mix on bottom of dish, then all of vegetable mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned. Meatballs can also be pan fried.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage, onion and mushrooms.
Drain.
Roll or stretch bread to overlap ends of 10 x 15-inch pan.
Spray pan with Pam. Spread half sausage down center, then half of cheese.
Repeat. Overlap ends and sides of bread.
Brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Slice; serve with picante sauce.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in a large rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Add cocoa, sugar and water.
Simmer over low heat until cocoa is dissolved.
Mix flour and water in cup until flour has no lumps.
Add to cocoa mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened.
When serving, add butter to hot gravy and serve with hot biscuits.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Brown.
Bake or fry until done.

title: apple cake
directions: Wash, peel, core and chop 2 cups apples. In bowl, pour sugar over chopped apples and let stand until juicy.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Beat eggs. Add all ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until browned.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Finish filling with whole milk.
Crank until ready.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve chocolate in 1/2 cup of boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream the egg yolk, sugar and Crisco.
Add alternately 3/4 cup of buttermilk and flour. Dissolve soda in 1/4 cup of buttermilk.
Add to batter plus salt, vanilla and chocolate.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 350° oven. Makes 3 nice size layers.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook, drain and arrange noodles onto a greased baking dish. Cook onion and butter and remove from heat.
Blend into cream cheese, cottage cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture onto the arranged noodles.
Combine soup and wine, then stir in all the seafood.
Spread 1/2 of this seafood mixture onto the cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/8 cup Parmesan and 1/4 cup of Cracker Barrel.
Repeat layers: noodles, cheese, seafood, Parmesan, Cracker Barrel.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly, then serve.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Place a large piece of aluminum foil in a baking pan and place brisket in center, shiny side next to meat.
Pour over liquid smoke and sprinkle with all other ingredients except barbecue sauce.
Wrap the foil over the meat and place in refrigerator for about 10 to 12 hours.
Transfer to a 300° oven and bake about 5 hours.
Uncover and pour barbecue sauce over meat.
Re-cover and bake 1 more hour.
When done, cool and slice against the grain. Trim off excess fat.
Good hot or cold.
Use Barbecue Sauce to follow or buy it.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and margarine.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Pour into baking dish; cover with cheese.
Heat 15 minutes at 350°.

title: little debbie cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and spices.
Add rest of ingredients. Roll into small balls and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Brown soup bones either in skillet over high heat or in 400° oven.
Combine all ingredients except barley and mushrooms in large soup kettle; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours.
Add barley; simmer 1 hour longer.
Add mushrooms; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove soup bones from kettle; let cool slightly.
Remove meat from bone; cut meat into pieces and return to soup.
Refrigerate overnight.
Skin any fat from surface; reheat soup and adjust seasonings before serving.

title: fudge pie
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one is added. Add melted chocolate, coffee and rum. Mix well. Stir in flour and pecans. Pour mixture into pie shells. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes two pies.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, or frost.

title: uncle jim's polenta and cheese
directions: Bring water and salt to boiling point in a deep pan.
Slowly add cornmeal to boiling water, stirring with a wooden spoon to prevent lumping.
Cook over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Cook 20 more minutes, stirring frequently.
The mixture should be on the soft side.
Add a little pepper.
Stir in the butter.
Turn out onto serving platter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve with your favorite sauce.
Good with sausage.

title: casserole of noodles italian style
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large pot, bring the water and 2 teaspoons salt to a boil. Add noodles and cook until they are done, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until hard boil without stirring, until hard crack stage (310°).
Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and food color; pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Butter hands and scissors; cut to desired sizes.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Scatter raw rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Lay chicken, skin side up, on top.
Mix soups and water and pour over chicken. Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut into eighths.
Put all ingredients into a large Ziploc plastic bag and shake to coat.
Remove potatoes from plastic bag and place in a single layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put 1/2 of the cookie crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Mix in powdered sugar; fold in Cool Whip.

title: hash brown cheesy potatoes
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Put potatoes in pan and arrange.
In another bowl mix rest of ingredients and only half of the cheese.
Pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gwen's apple cake
directions: Combine flour and baking powder and set aside.
Blend eggs and oil until light yellow.
Add and blend sugar, orange juice and vanilla for approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the flour mixture. Batter will be thick.
Peel and slice thinly 3 to 4 large apples (Rome or golden Delicious).
Grease and flour 2 (10-inch) tube or Bundt pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer batter, then apples (sprinkle with cinnamon).
Repeat.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, sage and milk.
Pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle corn bread mix over the mixture.
Pour chicken broth over the corn bread.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Note:
One-third cup mixture each = 9 crab cakes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 450° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: microwave basic meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, onion (can substitute 2 tablespoons dried onion flakes), crumbs, ketchup, milk and seasonings.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch glass loaf dish.
Spread last 2 tablespoons of ketchup evenly over top of loaf. Cover with plastic wrap, turning back one corner to vent.
Microwave at Medium-high (7) for 29 to 32 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn after half the time.
Let stand about 10 minutes to firm before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise.
Place in cold water with a little salt for a few minutes; drain.
Place in a buttered baking dish.
Add sugar, syrup and butter.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and soda.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour 5 (16 ounce) cans. Fill half full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Keeps for weeks in the refrigerator and freezes beautifully.
Yields 5 loaves.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Make paste of vinegar, cocoa and food coloring.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add alternately.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green pepper; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 3 hours.
Serve over pasta and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook a small Irish potato until tender and drain well.
Mash potato and add enough powdered sugar to make dough.
Roll dough between wax paper.
Remove one paper and spread peanut butter on dough.
Roll up like jelly roll and chill in refrigerator.
Cut in slices and eat.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook vegetables for a few minutes and drain.
Add cream of chicken soup and chicken.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until crust is done.
Cover top with French fried onions or chow mein noodles.
Put back in oven a few minutes to brown.

title: pickled hot peppers
directions: Dissolve salt in gallon of hot water.
Pour over peppers in glass or pottery bowl.
Let stand 12 to 18 hours in cool place. Rinse.
Drain.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Pack peppers into pint jars.
Bring liquid back to boil.
Pour into jars.
Seal.
Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.

title: daddy's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Beat together oil, buttermilk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix and add sugar, flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix.
Add boiling water and mix.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream and mix with oats, the butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, baking soda, vanilla, salt, flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Boil noodles until tender. Drain.
Add lasagna sauce out of box to meat and tomatoes (mashed up), the seasonings and the spaghetti sauce.
Stir well.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: smothered cabbage wedges
directions: In Dutch oven or large skillet, cook cabbage wedges in small amount of boiling salted water until tender (about 12 minutes). Drain.
Place wedges in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, cook pepper and onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk all at once, cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese and chili sauce. Spoon on wedges and bake 5 minutes more.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix well together the broccoli, cottage cheese, eggs or Egg Beaters, onion, melted oleo, salt and corn muffin mix.
Pour in greased 8 or 9-inch hot pan or skillet (can use Pam spray).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles and rinse in cold water.
Brown and drain beef. Add sauce and let simmer 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, Karo syrup (I use 1/2 cup dark and 1/2 cup light) and oleo. Add pecan halves. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden and done.
Cool before cutting.

title: macaronia salad
directions: Boil macaroni.
Drain and cool with cold water.
Add salt to taste.
Mix other ingredients together and add mayonnaise to desire.

title: southwestern tortilla wedges
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix salsa and sour cream.
Reserve half of the salsa mixture.
Mix the remaining salsa mixture, half of the bell pepper and the chicken.
Place 2 tortillas on ungreased cookie sheet and spread with chicken mixture.
Spread 2 tortillas with guacamole and place on chicken mixture.
Spread 2 more tortillas with refried beans and place on guacamole.
Top each stack with remaining salsa, a tortilla, bell pepper and cheese. Bake about 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and filling is hot.
Cut each stack into 8 wedges.
Makes 16 appetizers, 95 calories per appetizer.

title: chocolate graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into small squares and roll in confectioners sugar.
Can be frozen.

title: fresh cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite size flowerets.
Cut and stem broccoli, using tops only.
Add the sliced onion.
Mix last three ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Refrigerate and let stand 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
When done, pour reserved pineapple juice on warm cake.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: ham chowder
directions: Melt
butter and saute onion, potatoes and celery until almost cooked
through.
Mix
flour with 1/2 cup of the milk, then add it and the remaining milk to the potato mixture.
Add corn
and ham; heat until piping hot.
Serve hot with a salad or diced tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook 3 pounds of chicken.
Pull meat off and place in shallow baking dish (9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch).
Mix together the soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Spread mixture over chicken.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Crumble Ritz crackers and brown in butter. Spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grilled dove breast
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain and cool.
Add onion, Mozzarella, Cheddar and egg to sausage.
Roll out thawed bread dough onto greased cookie sheet.
Put meat mixture in center. Fold like envelope and seal ends.
Flip over so seam is on bottom. Brush top with a beaten egg.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain and add enchilada sauce, simmer.
Put tamales in baking dish at 300° for 3 minutes.
Remove and peel paper (it's easier if they're warm).
Place tamales in dish, cover with sauce, then layer chips, then cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: pickled corn or beans or both
directions: Shuck and clean corn.
Cook until done.
Cut corn off of the cob and cool completely.
Put in jars.
Take 6 cups cooled water that you cooked the corn in and 1/2 cup pickling salt.
Mix well and pour over corn in jars.
Seal and put in a cool place.

title: dynamites
directions: Cook on top of stove the tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and tomato paste.
Fry up ground beef and season to taste with oregano, salt and pepper.
(Note: 1/4 cup sugar takes away acid taste.)
Serve over bread, hot dog rolls, etc.
You can cook noodles and make chop suey with mixture.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Dump cherry pie filling on top of pineapple. Spread evenly. Spread dry cake mix from box, but do not mix.
Melt butter and pour evenly over top of cake mix.
Spread nuts over cake. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: devil's delight
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, water and butter.
Make "fingers" of dough about 3-inches long.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press an almond at the end of each "finger" to make a fingernail.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Frost cooled cookies with frosting.

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Add the boiling water to the All-Bran; soak for 5 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir until thoroughly blended. Store in a covered container in the refrigerator until ready to use.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue beef brisket
directions: Rub salts, tenderizer, sugar and Worcestershire sauce on each side of brisket.
Wrap brisket in foil and let marinate overnight. Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
During last 1/2 hour, open foil and drain all but 1/2 cup juice.
Add Open Pit barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Baste 2 to 3 times during last 1/2 hour.
Slice diagonally.
Pour desired amount of sauce over brisket slices.

title: easy manicotti with cheese
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce and water in saucepan to boiling.
Reduce heat and keep warm.
Mix together Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into cooked manicotti. Pour 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange filled manicotti in a single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over manicotti.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute peppers in margarine; season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add the beef broth; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add chopped parsley.
Sprinkle veal with ground black pepper and press into the meat.
Fry the veal fillets in hot oil 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Combine sauteed peppers and meat.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add tomatoes; simmer until thick.
Stir in chilies.
Make white sauce with remaining 2 tablespoons butter, flour and milk.
Add Tabasco sauce and salt.
Add both cheeses, stirring over medium until melted. Combine cheese sauce, tomato mixture and ground beef.
Serve in chafing dish, crock-pot or fondue pot with tortilla chips.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix, using 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Cool completely. Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and granulated sugar with mixer until creamy. Chop 8 candy bars finely. Fold cream cheese mixture and chopped candy into Cool Whip. Spread icing between layers and on top and sides of cake. Chop remaining 2 candy bars. Sprinkle half over top of cake and press the rest onto sides of cake.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Wash orange; cut into 8 wedges.
Remove white center; cut wedges into 3 or 4 pieces.
Remove any seeds; puree in electric blender.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add oil, orange puree and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Blend in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 15 x 3-inch pan.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 1 hour, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Remove from oven; cool cake in pan.
Cut into squares or slices.
Dust with confectioners sugar before serving.
Serves 12.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 3 quarts.
If cooking for two, soup can be frozen in serving size portions to enjoy months later.

title: tarheel apple pie
directions: Put
cream
cheese,
sugar
and
pudding
mix in 2 quart mixing
bowl.
Mix	thoroughly
until smooth, set aside.
Place apples
in	another
bowl and pour freshly squeezed lemon juice over slices.
Mix
well
and
set aside to stand for a few minutes.
Mix
together 2 tablespoons flour and sugar and sprinkle evenly in
bottom
of
crust.
Arrange half the apple slices in pie crust.	Measure 1/3 cup sugar and sprinkle 2 tablespoons of it over apple slices.	Spread	over
the
sugar,
half
of
the cheese mixture.
Arrange
remaining slices over the mixture and sprinkle with the
remainder
of
the
1/3	cup
sugar.
Spread evenly the rest of	the cheese mixture.
Put on top crust.	Dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour jello over marshmallows, then mix in pineapple and juice.
Add nuts.
Blend in Cool Whip real well.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add well beaten egg and milk. Stir until batter is smooth.
Peel and core apples.
Slice rather thin and dip in batter.
Fry fritters in hot, deep fat on both sides until golden brown.
Sprinkle liberally with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water over a medium heat until raisins are plump (about 15 minutes).
Drain raisins, reserving the liquid. Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1/2 cup, set aside.

title: country-house chocolate fudge
directions: Boil together the sugar, salt, oleo and milk.
Gently boil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Start timing after mixture has reached full gentle boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Add all chocolates; stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; stir until all mixed.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased pans or cookie sheets.
Cool several hours, then cut to store in airtight containers.
Keep cool.
One batch makes 12 pounds.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry
ones.
Stir until moist.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: summer vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine tomatoes, cucumbers, onion and radishes. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Add to vegetables and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Serve with slotted spoon. Yields 16 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Grate Cheddar in the cream cheese and mix well (use fork).
In another bowl, mix onion, green pepper, pimento, jalapeno pepper, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper and lemon juice.
Pour into cheese mixture and mix well.
Let chill about 2 hours.
Take out, make 2 balls.
Roll in pecans.

title: stuffed tomato salad
directions: Cut top off tomatoes and carefully scoop out meat.
Mix lemon juice, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cube avocado and tomato meat. Marinate in a bowl for 5 minutes. Add cooked ham. Toss and stuff the tomatoes with this salad.
Serve immediately on lettuce leaves. Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham(low-fat)
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, meat, onion and soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: spinach fettuccine with mushrooms and artichokes
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil in heavy, large skillet over high heat. Add mushrooms, garlic and thyme and saute until mushrooms are golden, about 6 minutes.
Add bell pepper and saute 3 minutes. Add artichoke hearts, cream, stock and 1/2 cup cheese and simmer 3 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook fettuccine in large pot of boiling, salted water until just tender but still firm to bite.
Drain.
Transfer to bowl.
Toss with remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Pour sauce over.
Serve, passing additional cheese separately.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook chicken, half at a time, until browned.
Add onion and pepper; cook about 5 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: spaghetti-pizza style
directions: Break spaghetti into small pieces and cook according to package; drain.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Toss into spaghetti.
Spread into a greased 11 x 18-inch pan.
(For deeper dish, use a 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Crumble hamburger over the sauce.
Put on onion, green pepper, garlic salt and any other spices you prefer.
Arrange pepperoni on top.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: mushrooms and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, covered, until liquid is absorbed, no more than 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Put onion, broccoli, water and bouillon cubes in large pot. Cook on medium until vegetables are tender. Melt margarine in saucepan; add flour. Stir until creamy. Add slowly to vegetables; stir well. Add milk, Cheez Whiz, salt and pepper to taste. Stir well and heat until cheese is completely melted.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix margarine and crumbs.
Pat out into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat 10 minutes.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Cover with pineapple drained well.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: granny fussell's pecan pie(yields 8 servings)
directions: Prebake one 9-inch pie shell and set aside.
Break 3 eggs in bowl and let come to room temperature.
Put Karo, sugar and melted oleo in pot and mix.
Slowly mix in eggs and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in pecans and cook 1 more minute.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell and put into 400° oven for 15 minutes (or until sealed over good).

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated. Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly and firmly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yield:
24 squares, 2 x 2 inches.

title: sunflower cheese snacks
directions: Mix and shape in balls.
Flatten and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in a little oil in a heavy round roasting pot.
Remove roast.
Pour off fat.
Add 2 cups hot water and bouillon; stir.
Put roast back in pot.
Add sliced onion around roast.
Spread some mustard on top and sides of roast. Cover.
Roast in oven at 250°
for 3 to 4 hours.
Let roast set 15 minutes before slicing.
Add flour and water to juice in pan. Stir until boiling.
Cook a few more minutes for delicious gravy.

title: eatable play dough
directions: Mix.
Let children play and then eat!!!

title: blackberry salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water.
Add either frozen blackberries or canned blackberries.
Put in refrigerator to set. Blend cream cheese with sugar and small amount of whipped cream. Whip 1 pint whipping cream (or balance after removed) with vanilla.
Blend the 2 mixtures with mixer and carefully spread on top of jello mixture.
Store in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice; stir to thoroughly dissolve.
Chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill in shallow pan or individual molds until firm.
Unmold on lettuce.
Serve with mayonnaise on top (if you wish).

title: texas dessert
directions: Work butter, flour and nuts like pastry. Press into 8 x 12 x 2 Pyrex dish. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: philadelphia rice pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and place in a 3-quart covered saucepan.
Bring to a simmer on the top of the stove and then place, covered, in a 300° oven.
Bake without disturbing or stirring for 2 hours and 45 minutes.
The pudding will almost caramelize and become a pale golden color.
It's just wonderful on a cool fall day!

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients with a spoon.
Fold in the sour cream and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: tiny puffs
directions: Boil water and butter/margarine over lowered heat; add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan (about 1 minute).
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet about 3 inches apart. Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes until puffed and golden.
Cool; freeze.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown venison, onion and bacon.
Drain and add beans, molasses, ketchup, powdered mustard and brown sugar.
Gently stir together and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes or heat through on top of stove, stirring often to keep from sticking.

title: drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in boiler and bring to a boil.
Continue boiling 1 minute, stirring all the time.
Add oatmeal and vanilla extract.
Mix all together; drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Heat butter in skillet over low heat; add garlic.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook until bubbly, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Return to heat.
Stir and boil one minute.
Cook over low heat and add Mozzarella cheese, onion, basil and pepper.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted. Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Spread 1 1/2 cups cheese sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with three noodles. Spread with Ricotta cheese.
Pour 1/4 of remaining cheese sauce over Ricotta cheese and top again with 3 noodles.
Top noodles with shrimp, crabmeat and 1/2 of remaining sauce.
Place remaining noodles over seafood and pour remaining sauce over top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, powdered. sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well, add vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture.

title: party dream salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese, sour cream, powdered sugar, lemon juice and salt until light and fluffy. Fold in oranges, cherries, nuts, bananas and whipping cream. Turn into shallow salad bowl.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All. Mix soup and sour cream with Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Top with grated cheese. Mix together crushed Ritz crackers with melted margarine and place on top. Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese blueberry pie
directions: Cream together.
Soften cream cheese with sugar until fluffy. Mix Dream Whip by directions on box.
Fold in cream cheese.
Fill cracker crust.
Top with blueberries and chill overnight.
(Any kind of fruit may be used.)

title: white trash candy
directions: Melt Candiquik in microwave (cut into smaller pieces).
Mix cereals, pretzels and peanuts in very large bowl.
Pour melted Candiquik over cereal mixture.
Mix well.
Line 2 large pans with wax paper.
Pour mixture in pans.
Spread out; let harden. Break into pieces.

title: krispy chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into melted margarine.
Roll into Rice Krispies until well coated.
Lay on broiler pan and bake, uncovered, not broil, for 1 hour at 350°. You can spray pan with Pam for easier cleaning.

title: black cats
directions: In double boiler, melt margarine and marshmallows. Stir in salt and mix until smooth.

title: marinated sirloin
directions: Cut steak in cubes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate overnight.
Next day heat skillet thoroughly.
Grease it sparingly.
Cook the meat cubes in the skillet to desired doneness.
Baste with marinade juice, if necessary.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Bring 6 cups water to boiling; add salt and outer leaves of cabbage (about 12).
Simmer 3 minutes.
Drain leaves, reserving 2 cups liquid.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix
gelatin
according
to
package directions.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in nuts, celery and cranberry sauce. Mix well and pour in dish.	Chill until solid.

title: sopapillas
directions: Knead all ingredients together.
Let stand while heating oil in a shallow skillet (about 1/3 full).
Roll out dough; cut into any shape.
Put into hot oil, brown on both sides and drain on paper towel.

title: mexican taco salad
directions: Drain kidney beans and olives.
Chop up lettuce, tomato and onion.
Fry hamburg; drain fat, then mix taco flavor package in meat.
Let meat mixture cool off a bit.
Toss lettuce, tomato, onion, olives and beans.
Sprinkle hamburg on top.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of meat.
Crumble Doritos on top of cheese. Serve in salad bowls with dressings and hot sauce according to taste.
It's a meal in itself.

title: pork chops with cheese and beer
directions: Grill the chops under moderate grill for 7 to 10 minutes depending on the thickness. Turn over and grill for 7 to 10 minutes until cooked through.
Mix together the cheese, mustard and brown ale.
Spread over the chops and grill until the cheese has melted. Transfer to a warm serving plate and garnish with tomato halves and watercress sprigs.

title: banana muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add milk, egg, shortening and bananas.
Mix well or until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full, sprinkle each top with mixture of 1 tablespoon white sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot.

title: chrusciki(angel wings)
directions: Blend eggs, sour cream and whiskey; add salt to flour and blend together with first mixture until a ball forms (firm but not sticky).
Cut into pieces and roll out dough thin (using Wondra flour) and cut into strips about 6 to 8-inches long and about 1-inch wide; cut slit in center of each piece and pull one end through the slit.
Fry in Crisco in electric wok or electric frypan (I use wok) about 30 to 45 seconds on each side (very lightly browned); drain on paper towel and cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Do not use oil; it is too heavy.
Use shortening (about 3/4 to a full can).

title: pork and cheese stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells in 3 quarts boiling, salted water for 8 to 10 minutes.
Gently drain.
Rinse in cold water and set aside.

title: taco rice skillet
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add tomatoes, reserving juice and adding water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, reduce and simmer, stirring occasionally until most of the moisture is absorbed.
Top with cheese.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: You will need a 2 x 9 x 9-inch baking pan, ungreased.

title: carrot cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening; stir in carrots, then honey and eggs.
Gradually stir in all other ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: congealed tomato salad
directions: Bring tomatoes to a boil and add dry jello.
Mix well and allow to jell.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: vegetable trio with zippy sauce
directions: Combine ingredients except vegetables.
Heat and stir over low heat, just until warm through.
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain and mix.
Pour hot sauce over vegetables.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: remade pickles
directions: Take dill pickles out of dill jar.
Wipe dry, then place them in hot vinegar from sweet pickles.
Heat for 2 minutes.
Store in jar; let set for 2 days before using.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, cocoa, salt and milk to the margarine. Stir constantly until melted. Bring these ingredients to a full boil. Boil for exactly 1 minute. Remove from heat after 1 minute; add peanut butter.
Stir until melted. Add quick oats. Stir together. Drop by teaspoon onto a sheet of foil.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients until vegetables are tender; add noodles, tomatoes, parsley and basil.
So quick to make and so good to taste.

title: sponge cake with 7 minute frosting
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until thick and lemon color. Gradually beat in sugar and part of water, flavoring and flour, then remaining water.
Beat egg whites with baking powder and salt until they hold a point, then fold in yolk mixture.
Bake in ungreased tube center pan at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: easy, easy crepes
directions: Mix milk, vanilla and eggs, then add the sifted flour gradually and beat with a wire whisk.
In a large skillet, drop 1 teaspoon of oil, then pour batter into skillet to cover the bottom.
When the top of the crepe disappears, dry then flip and cook the other side.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Butter a casserole dish.
Place potatoes in dish.
Pour soup over potatoes; put remainder of margarine on potatoes.
Sprinkle onion on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: summer pasta
directions: Dice all ingredients together.
Do not cook.
Serve over cold pasta.

title: twin meat loaves
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Add eggs and beat.
Add meat, salt, pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and poultry seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into two loaves.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake,
uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with catsup or chili sauce and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beans and noodles
directions: Wash beans. Cook with water in a large pot with salt and 2-inch square of salt pork until almost done, 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Keep plenty of water in beans. When almost done, add the noodles. Cook until noodles are done.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown the hamburger with
the onion and drain.
Add the tomato paste, sauce and
tomatoes
or juice.
Add the parsley, oregano, garlic salt
and
Italian seasoning to taste.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Cook the noodles as directed;
drain.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Place sliced mushrooms in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with chicken pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve with rice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms and wash.
Chop stems, onion and garlic and saute in olive oil about 10 minutes.
Then add parsley, salt and pepper.
Saute another 5 minutes and remove from stove. Add 4 tablespoons of bread crumbs and eggs; mix well.
Fill each mushroom cap with filling and sprinkle with bread crumbs and oil. Place in greased baking pan in hot oven (400°) for 25 minutes.

title: breakfast sundaes
directions: In four small bowls (glass or plastic), layer 2 Tbsp. each of yogurt, granola, bananas and oranges.
Repeat layers.
Serve immediately.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender; drain.
Melt oleo; stir in flour and add milk gradually.
Cook at medium heat until thick.
Add cheese and stir until blended.
Put 1/2 carrots in 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover with onions and repeat.
Save 1/2 onions.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; add remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 standard loaf pans. Sift together flour and baking soda.
In a large bowl, lightly beat egg whites.
Mix in oil and rind, using your hands.
Stir in brown sugar and flour mixture until just blended.
Fold in strawberries and nuts.
Do not overblend or bread will be tough.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until done.

title: nanny cook's easy cookies
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Do not use a mixer.
When well mixed, drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 8 to 9 minutes.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar and baking powder. Cut in shortening until mixture is the size of a pea. In a separate bowl, combine egg, water and vinegar. Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons water over flour mixture. Mix lightly with a fork. Add remaining egg mixture. Mix only until pastry holds together. Gather dough together and press into a ball. Wrap in wax paper. Chill 15 minutes. Roll out on floured pastry cloth. Makes two to three 9-inch crusts.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 to 60 minutes.
Serve with oyster crackers.
Makes approximately 7 cups.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Brown chopped onion in butter.
Add garlic powder.
Add flour; stir in milk, tomatoes, salmon, corn and dill.
Bring to boil; add shredded Mozzarella cheese.

title: lemon tart potatoes
directions: Cube and cook potatoes in 1 inch boiling water; drain. Combine the rest of the ingredients; toss with potatoes.
Spoon into doubled layer of aluminum foil.
Wrap tightly.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Place on grill with medium coals. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Position the racks in the top and lower third of the oven and preheat to 350°.
In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda, salt, allspice, cinnamon and mace.
In another large bowl, combine the butter and sugar and with a hand held electric mixer, mix on low speed until just incorporated.
Raise the speed to high and mix until light and fluffy.
(Occasionally turn the mixer off, and scrape the side of the bowl down with a rubber spatula.)
Add the brown sugar and mix until incorporated.
Add the eggs to the butter mixture, one at a time, waiting for the first one to be fully incorporated before adding the last.
Mix in the vanilla. Reduce the mixer's speed to low.
Add the flour mixture, little by little, until a smooth dough is formed (scrape the bowl down occasionally).
Turn off the machine, stir in the oats, raisins and pecans with a rubber spatula.
Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
Using a spoon, drop heaping tablespoons of the dough onto the sheets, spaced about 2 inches apart.

title: onion supreme
directions: Drain onions.
Heat margarine in skillet.
Add mushrooms and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from heat.
With slotted spoon, remove mushrooms and set aside.
Heat soup and add milk gradually until soup is creamy.
Arrange half of onions and half of mushrooms in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with half of mushroom soup and 3 slices cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy hot meatballs
directions: Mix together well; roll into balls.
Brown in skillet or in oven; drain.

title: sausage dish
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: cream cheese - cherry bundt cake
directions: Blend together cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together using only 2 cups of flour.
Blend with sugar mixture.
Mix remaining flour with cherries and nuts and fold into batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.
Pour glaze over cake.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese.
Toss ingredients gently.
Spoon into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle potato chips and cheese on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: confetti vegetables
directions: Boil water in a Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Heat all ingredients to boiling.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, margarine, salt, cheese, onion, sour cream, black pepper and cream of chicken soup.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Place onion rings on top of potatoes.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Soften cream cheese. Wipe mushrooms with wet towel or cloth to cleanse.
Remove stems and chop. Blend cream cheese, salt, garlic, onion, soy sauce, half of the bacon and mushroom stems until creamy.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture and place in shallow pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining bacon and parsley. Serve immediately.

title: shrimp dip for crackers
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Rinse and drain shrimp.
Break up with a fork.
Mix with onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Make into a ball.
Chill.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: In a large saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling water until done. Drain and place in a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to form a smooth paste.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add cheese.
Stir just until melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: "ugly duckling" cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, fruit cocktail and eggs. Mix for 2 minutes or until all the ingredients are blended well.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute mushrooms and chopped pepper 5 minutes in 2 tablespoons butter.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and blend in flour and add chicken stock slowly.
When thick and smooth, stir in chicken, salt and pepper.
Beat egg yolks and add mixture gradually, then combine and serve hot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place torn bread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Brown sausage or bacon and drain.
Spoon sausage or bacon over bread. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over sausage.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, dry mustard, salt and dash of pepper to eggs. Mix well.
Pour over ingredients in the pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot buttered lemonade
directions: Combine water, sugar, lemon peel and lemon juice in slow cooker.
Cover and heat on low heat for 4 to 6 hours.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Put prepared vegetables through a food chopper and squeeze through a cloth until dry.
Add chopped eggs, salad dressing and salt.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, margarine and vanilla together.
Add the powdered sugar.

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute onions and celery until tender.
Put in large bowl.
Cook and drain meat; add to first mixture.
Saute 1 can bean sprouts in own juice; add to mixture.
Chop eggs very fine; add to rest. Sprinkle with soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Put small amount of mixture on wrapper and roll, sealing with water and cornstarch mixture.
Deep fry until of brownness desired.
Makes 40 to 50 small egg rolls or 20 to 25 large.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham crackers, 1/2 cup sugar and oleo.
Pat gently in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Put on top of crust.
Bake for 40 minutes at 275°.
Top with pie filling, then Cool Whip.

title: chef's salad bowl
directions: Rub salad bowl with 1 cut clove of garlic.
Make French dressing in salad bowl.
Add lettuce, broken in pieces.
Arrange vegetables and sliced egg over lettuce.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, together.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Then bake in casserole (covered) for 1 hour at 350°. Serve over rice.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Start in cold oven.
Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar gradually and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add whipping cream and flour alternately, beating well after each.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain juice from berries and save juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add berry juice, mayonnaise and salt.
Blend with rotary beater.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes.
Fold in strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar and beat smoothly.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter in 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Italian Cream Frosting.

title: hot kolbassi dip
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart bowl, microwave cream cheese, uncovered, on High for 1 minute; stir in sour cream, milk, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Add kolbassi, half of the onions and Parmesan cheese; stir.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining onion.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Boil ingredients slowly until fudge forms a soft ball in cup of cold water.
Let cool and stir until fudge loses its gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: sweet peanuts
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 15 minutes until sugar crystallizes on peanuts.
Spread onto baking sheet coated with Pam.
Sprinkle with salt (optional).
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Turn peanuts after 15 minutes.

title: french fried chicken
directions: Combine pancake mix, salt and water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Dip chicken in batter; drain.
Cook chicken in hot oil (350°) until tender, about 10 minutes on each side.

title: fay's meringue for pies
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.	Gradually beat in sugar, sprinkling a little at a time over the surface of egg white. Add vanilla.
Pile lightly on top of the pie (thoroughly cover). Seal the edge.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients; add milk and margarine.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 20 minutes in a 15 x 20-inch greased pan.
While hot out of the oven, spread with peanut butter.
Refrigerate.
Melt 2 (8 ounce) Hershey chocolate bars and spread on top of peanut butter.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and cook first 4 ingredients to harder than soft ball stage.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Dissolve thoroughly in candy.
Pour immediately in pan.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Heat and drain vegetables.
Add butter.
Start with layer of crackers, then vegetables, then cheese.
Keep layering each until all are used.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Heat until bubbly.

title: copper pennies
