directions: Bring everything but he carrots to a boil.
Pour over carrots.
Marinate overnight in a glass container in the refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Mix beer, salt, egg and Bisquick (enough to make batter thick).
Dip fish in batter.
Fry in 1/2-inch hot oil until golden brown, turning once.

title: salmon ring
directions: Generously grease a 5-cup ovenproof ring mold.
Set aside. In a mixing bowl, drain and flake salmon.
Add bread crumbs, eggs, celery, green pepper, onion and lemon juice.
Separate crescent rolls in triangles.
Arrange triangles in ring mold, alternating points and wide ends of triangles so dough drapes over center and outer edges.
Pat the dough lightly to line the mold.
Pack the salmon mixture into the dough lined mold.
Turn the ends of dough over the salmon to cover.
Press to seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and dip in walnuts.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop onions, lettuce and tomatoes.
Toss with grated cheese, French dressing and hot sauce to taste.
Crunch and add Doritos chips.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add salt and drained kidney beans.
Simmer 10 minutes, then add to cold salad.
Decorate with chips, tomato slices and avocado slices, if desired.
Serve pronto!

title: crock pot chicken & sausage gumbo
directions: Make roux in a heavy saucepan by stirring together the flour and cooking oil until smooth. Cook over medium high heat for 5 minutes stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium, cook and stir constantly about 15 minutes more, or until roux is dark reddish brown. Cool. In a 3-1/2, 4 or 5 quart crock pot place the water and stir in roux. To the water and roux mixture add the smoked sausage, chicken, okra, onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic, salt, pepper, and red pepper, also corn, tomatoes, and green beans, if desired. Mix all together. Cover and cook on low heat for 6 to 7 hours, or on high heat for 3
to 3-1/2 hours.

title: crabmeat souffle (or shrimp)
directions: Spread 1/2 bread cubes in baking dish, 8 x 12-inch (oiled or Pam).
Mix shrimp, mayonnaise, onion, pepper, celery and soup (salt and pepper).
Spread over bread cubes.
Put remaining bread on top.
Blend milk and eggs.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bring to room temperature.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (maybe a little longer).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie.
Remove to wire rack.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: In large bowl mix macaroni, chicken, cucumber, radishes and Cheddar cheese.
Blend in the mayonnaise with Italian salad dressing; salt and pepper to taste.
Just before serving, toss in half can French-fried onions and sprinkle remainder on top of salad.

title: cheddar-broccoli cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In a small saucepan combine soup and margarine.
Heat over low heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
In a large bowl combine flour, meal, sugar and baking powder.
Add soup mixture, egg, corn and cheese.
Stir until batter is just combined.
Do not over mix.
Scoop batter into prepared pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
I usually use an iron skillet instead of a pan.

title: cold-chaser chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in large Dutch oven, crock-pot or stew pot; fill pot 3/4 full with water.
Add all other ingredients, except okra. Simmer for 3 hours.
Add okra; cook 1/2 hour longer.
Remove bones from chicken; replace meat in soup.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding together.
Add sour cream and half of Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add bananas and wafers.
Mix by hand.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: grandma's banana pudding
directions: Heat milk over medium heat until hot.
Beat eggs and add cold milk.
Stir into hot milk.
Mix sugar and corn starch together in small bowl.
Stir into milk.
Continue stirring over medium heat. Add vanilla and butter.
Slice bananas.
Line the bowl with vanilla cookies.
For soft cookies add hot pudding over mixture.
For crisp cookies, cool pudding before adding.

title: fried rice
directions: Take a slice of beef liver.
Cut into finger strips; salt and pepper, then roll in powdered milk and flour.
Fry in bacon grease or Crisco.
Delicious if you like liver.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix egg yolks with a little milk.
Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, in saucepan.
Cook until oleo melts and mixture is thick. Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer until creamy.
Beat egg whites. Pour filling in cool pie shells.
Top with beaten egg whites. Brown in oven.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine; add eggs.
Beat
for 1 minute at medium speed. Add remaining ingredients	and beat for a few minutes. Pour into pie shell.	Bake at
for 45 minutes.	Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pecans) together.
Line unbaked pie crust with whole pecans.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat yolks and salt.
Add enough flour to make a firm dough. Roll out and cut to desired size.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cook until tender.
Can use the egg whites for an angel food cake.

title: pinto beans
directions: Will need to use crock-pot.

title: veal stew
directions: Brown veal and add the onion, broth and seasoning, water, tomato sauce, thyme, rosemary and allspice.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook until veggies are tender.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain.
Place in layers in a greased baking dish:
noodles, peas, carrots, onions and tuna.
Sprinkle seasoning over each layer.
Drizzle margarine over top and bake 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce in bottom of 8 x 12-inch dish.
Layer with celery, green peas, pepper and onion.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble between paper towels.
Stir sugar into mayonnaise; spread over top of vegetables.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon and cheese over top.
Best if prepared a day ahead of serving and refrigerated.

title: texas first lady laura bush's cowboy cookies
directions: Creme butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Add dry ingredients until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine beans; divide into four equal batches, about 3 3/4 cups each.
To make one batch of soup:
Wash one batch of beans.
Place in a large kettle; add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Drain and rinse beans. Return to kettle; add spices and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove spices.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Yield:
One batch makes 14 servings (3 1/2-quarts).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° until done.

title: scotch parfait
directions: Blend honey and Scotch (this takes a little time to incorporate the Scotch into the honey).
Whip cream until stiff. Fold honey mixture into cream.
Spoon into parfait glasses and freeze overnight.
Prior to serving, top with grated chocolate, almonds, and a cherry.
If desired you may purchase chocolate dessert cups from a gourmet food shop
and spoon the mixture into cups prior to serving.
This needs to made 24 hours in advance. This does keep well in freezer.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add sugar slowly to beaten egg whites.
Fold in chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Drop on cookie sheets. Place cookies in oven and turn oven off.
Take out next morning.

title: peach or strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press in jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Make a filling with 1 cup powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Place fruit over filling and top with glaze.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and top with cheese. Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: one meal casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions with seasoning; drain.
Add mushroom soup, potatoes, sour cream and water.
Simmer until potatoes are done.
Serves about 4 to 6.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° to 400° oven.

title: chicken burrito
directions: Mix chicken, grated cheese and onions.
Spoon mixture into flour tortilla and roll tightly.
Lay seam side down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over tortilla.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix 2 slightly beaten eggs and 1 teaspoon nutmeg in a 1-quart casserole, slowly stir in rice mixture and mix well. Place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Cool 1 hour.

title: indian stew
directions: Cook hamburger with onion and chili powder; drain.
Add tomato sauce and corn.
Let simmer.
Mix cornbread according to package, but reduce water by about 1/4 to thicker consistency.
Drop by teaspoon into stew mixture.
Let cook until cornbread dumplings are done, about 10 minutes.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, stirring in.
Then add salt, flour and Karo syrup.
Fold nut meats in flour and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, then lower to 325° and cook until done.

title: sugar cookies(seed cookies)
directions: Mix butter, vanilla, powdered sugar, sugar, 2 eggs and salt. Combine with mixer.
Add the flour, cream of tartar and baking soda mixture.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Roll into balls and dip in seeds.
Press on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Watch closely; they burn easily.

title: (five) bean barbecue
directions: Saute the onion in bacon grease.
Drain off fat.
Make a sauce of the first 5 ingredients. Drain the beans and mix in the diced cheese.
Pour the sauce over the beans.
Place in casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours. Serves about 16 to 20. Especially good with pork, roast, etc.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring to boil and then add 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup of milk with beaten egg, then add another 1/2 cup milk with pudding mix. Simmer for 45 minutes and let cool.

title: apple and pork casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in shortening until tender.
Stir in soup, sugar and cinnamon.
Add pork and apples.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.
Prepare potatoes using 1/4 cup milk and a dash of pepper.
Blend egg into potatoes. Spoon potatoes in 6 mounds atop pork mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir together Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready
to serve.

title: quick chicken
directions: Mix soup, milk and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add chow mein noodles and boneless chicken, cut into pieces with liquid.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and pasta roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place hot noodles under cold running water until cool enough to handle; drain and set aside.
In medium bowl, combine soup, mustard, milk and 1/2 cup Swiss cheese; pour half the soup mixture into 10-inch round or 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine spinach, Parmesan cheese, egg and 1/2 can French fried onions; stir until well blended.
Fold each ham slice in half lengthwise and place on one end of cooled lasagna noodle.
Top ham with 1/4 cup spinach mixture.
Roll up noodles tightly, jelly-roll style.
With sharp knife, cut roll-ups into halves.
Arrange in dish, ruffled-side up.
Pour remaining soup mixture over roll-ups.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining Swiss cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken glop
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix the onion soup mix, cream of mushroom soup and the sour cream until blended (a few lumps are required).
Rinse the chicken breasts and pat dry (see, boneless are easier to work with, right?).
Place the breasts in a nonmetallic baking dish.
Spread the soup mixture evenly over the chicken.
Cover.
Place into oven.
(You did remember to preheat, didn't you?)
Cook for about 4 hours or until done.
This can be speeded up by cooking at 350°, but it leaves a yeechy crust around the edge.
Enjoy.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Crust:
Beat 1 egg and brush over the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: cheese beef and celery
directions: Freeze steak partially (may use cheap cut of steak).
Slice thin while still partially frozen and brown.
Stir-fry with meat the celery, onions, carrots and garlic (if desired).
Add gravy of the beef bouillon, cornstarch and soy sauce.
May add more water if want thinner or to cook longer.
Add the bean sprouts and mushrooms with juice.
Simmer until flavors are blended and vegetables are well done.

title: refrigerator spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Place in air tight covered container and store in refrigerator.
As needed, spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° about 20 minutes.
Will keep 1 week in refrigerator.
No rising time required.

title: mama's lemon chiffon pudding
directions: Cook pudding mix, water, sugar and egg yolks to boil.
Cool. Beat egg whites until stiff and add an additional 1/4 cup sugar. Fold into pudding mix.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: celery salad with apples and pecans
directions: With paring knife, cut away coarse outer layer of celery.
Cut celery into chunks suitable for grating.
Using large grater or food processor, grate 3 cups.
Peel, core and grate apple; add to celery.
Beat together egg yolks, mustard, salt and pepper. Gradually add the oil, drop by drop at first, then continue beating in very gradually until mixture is thick and creamy.
Add lemon juice to taste.
Pour over celery and apple.
Fold in pecans just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: iva's instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep dry mixture in tightly covered container.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons of mixture per 1 cup hot water or to taste.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut a slice from stem end of each pepper. Remove seeds and preboil peppers 10 minutes. Mix cooked meat with moistened bread crumbs. Add salt, pepper and onion. Stuff peppers with mixture and place in baking pan. Add water. Bake in moderate 375° oven for 30 minutes, basting frequently. Serves 6.

title: golden-glazed chicken breasts
directions: In small bowl, thoroughly combine soup mix, preserves and water and set aside.
In foil-lined broiler pan, arrange chicken breasts and peppers. Top with soup mixture and broil 10 minutes or until chicken is done, turning once.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: swiss mocha
directions: Shake in jar to blend.
Process in blender until powdery.
Use 1 level tablespoon per 6 ounces of boiling water per serving. Delicious and much cheaper than commercial brands.

title: ham and bean stew
directions: In a slow cooker, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and cook on low for 7 hours or until the potatoes are tender. Yields 6 servings.

title: excellent pralines
directions: Mix together the buttermilk, sugar and soda until sugar is dissolved.
Place on low to medium heat; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Beat until glossy and begins thickening.
Spoon out on greased wax paper.
If it gets too thick to spoon out, put it back on the heat for a minute or so.
It will gradually turn brown while cooking.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In crock-pot, combine tomatoes with juice, red beans and sausage.
Allow to slow cook all day, then serve over fluffy rice. Mexican cornbread and a green salad complete this meal.
(No other seasoning is needed, the sausage and tomatoes are enough.)

title: cheese toast
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and cayenne pepper.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Stir in cheese and cook until melted. Add salt to taste.
Beat 2 tablespoons of hot cheese mix into the yolks.
Return yolk-cheese mixture to saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat, gently fold in the egg whites. Serve on toast.

title: hot dog salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients in large stock pot. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil for 20 minutes. Fill cleaned and sterilized jars and seal.

title: asparagus sandwich mix
directions: Drain asparagus well.
Mash with fork.
Combine with remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate over night.

title: play dough
directions: Mix hot water and salt in a bowl for 1 minute (salt will not dissolve, but will reduce in size).
Add flour until all water is absorbent.
Knead until smooth.
If dough is a bit dry, add sprinkle of water.
If dough is a bit sticky, add a bit of flour. Add food coloring to make colored dough.
Store in airtight containers.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and salsa.
Spread on a flat serving platter.
Cover and chill in refrigerator for 2 hours. Just before serving, chop lettuce, tomatoes and black olives. Spread in that order over cheese mixture.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Stir well.
Pour into shells and bake 15 minutes at 250°. Turn up to 300° until a knife comes out clean.

title: not so sweet pecan pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients together adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked 10-inch
pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Combine ingredients and stuff lightly into meat, allowing room for expansion; or use as desired.

title: vegetable bar
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet pan with rolls.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes, at temperature on carton; cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing; spread on rolls.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables on dressing.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into small squares.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large (big) bowl.
Beat at medium speed (about 650 r.p.m.); maybe should use an electric mixer.
Add egg; beat just a little more.
Combine (yes, again) the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed (you guess the r.p.m.'s).
Roll this stuff into balls the size of huge marbles. Put on baking sheet; flatten with a nonstick fork (to be invented yet).
Bake one cookie sheet at a time for 7 to 8 minutes, or until done.
Do not burn; this makes the cookies tastes awful. Cool on a piece of foil less than 4 feet long.
Now, eat them.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and grated cheese.
Add sausage and mix well. Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet; add bell peppers and onion. Drain.
Stir in soup, sliced olives, salsa and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, bay leaf and celery together.
When done, cut chicken in cubes.
Cook macaroni in chicken broth.
Make white sauce with fat, milk and flour.
Cut cheese in cubes and add to white sauce.
Stir until melted.
Add mushrooms, pepper and onion. Combine all and put in large oiled baking dish or 3 small ones. Top with buttered crumbs and bake 30 minutes.

title: mortal sin bars
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 2/3 cup evaporated milk. Batter will be very
thick.
Spread half the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread remaining batter over all.
Sprinkle with additional nuts, if desired.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken and pineapple
directions: In skillet or wok, saute chicken strips in oil or margarine. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and stir constantly for 3 minutes. Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Stir for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, corn syrup, salt and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix flour and soda and add to shortening-sugar mixture.
When all ingredients are completely mixed, form dough into one-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheets two inches apart.
Bake in a very slow oven at 200° to 250° until light golden brown.
Cool slightly before removing with a spatula.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add egg yolks, vanilla, soda, salt and water. Sift in flour. Add buttermilk. Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat into mixture. Bake in three 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Turn out. Let cool.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: On 1/2 graham cracker, place 1 marshmallow.
Microwave until marshmallow swells up.
Then clamp on 2 squares of Hershey bar and another 1/2 of graham cracker.
Let this cool few seconds and it's ready.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine 1/4 cup lukewarm water, yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar; blend well.
Add Crisco or oil, sugar, egg, salt, 1 cup lukewarm water and flour.
Mix all together.
Knead like making biscuits. Let rise for 2 or 2 1/2 hours in a warm place, then work down like you do for biscuits.
Cut out; put in greased pan.
Let set for about 2 hours.
Cook at 375° or 400° until well done.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
In a large skillet, heat corn oil over medium high heat.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic; stir fry for 2 minutes or until crisp tender.
Remove from skillet.
Stir fry 1/2 of the pork at a time for 3 minutes. Return all the pork to the skillet.
In a bowl, stir together the pineapple juice, cornstarch, corn syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and ketchup.
Stir this mixture into skillet with pork; add green pepper mixture and pineapple, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add zucchini and nuts. Spray two pans with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Add onions, green pepper and garlic to hot oil in a skillet. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until tender.
Stir in meat.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour. Yields about 8 servings.

title: betty's chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, pepper, garlic and mushrooms in butter. Boil spaghetti in broth.
Put cheese in spaghetti. After it's cooked, turn burner off.
Let cheese melt. Add vegetables and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Bake in
a 350° oven in casserole dish for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: supper steaks
directions: Flour cube steak; brown in small amount of shortening. Place in pan; sprinkle with onion soup. Put drained mushrooms on. Cover with sliced onion. Mix beef gravy with water and pour over onions; do not stir. Cover with foil. Bake in 8 x 13-inch pan at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: grannies grand chocolate pies
directions: Poke holes in crusts with a fork to keep from puffing up while baking.
Bake at 350° until crusts are lightly browned.
Set aside.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Add the ingredients in roasting pan.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes until chicken browns.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus as directed.
Combine soup and milk, stirring until blended.
Layer 1/2 each of water chestnuts, asparagus, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers until finished.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: tomato cabbage
directions: Cook bacon first.
Keep fat to cook your onions in.
Wash and drain your cabbage.
Put in your onions and tomatoes and bring to boil.
Then put in drained cabbage and seasoning.
Turn down and simmer until done to your taste.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo with baking chocolate.
Combine with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° in greased pan until done.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix milk and pudding together in a medium size bowl.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the whole graham crackers. Pour 1/2 of the pudding mixture on first layer of graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers and pour the rest of the pudding mixture on top.
Spread chocolate frosting on the last layer of graham crackers, then put them on top of pudding. Refrigerate.

title: barbecued pork and beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter; mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased small casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 2 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat. Add 1 1/2 packages taco seasoning mix and water according to directions on seasoning mix. Simmer according to seasoning mix directions.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place all ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil.
Cook about 8 minutes.
Pour into casserole and bake for 1 hour.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Over medium heat, melt marshmallows and butter together.
Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Fold in corn flakes and mix well. Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper.
Working quickly with buttered fingers, form into little wreaths.
Decorate with candies.
They will firm up as they cool.
Makes about 24.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order and bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham salad spread
directions: First 3 ingredients are
ground
up
with food chopper. Add pimentos,
pepper and
salad
dressing,
then
mix
well. Double the recipe for larger
amount
or for party sandwiches. Make ahead for extra seasoned taste and keep refrigerated.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In a gallon jar, mix vinegar, water and celery seed.
Add juice from beets and peppers.
Layer beets, onions, eggs and peppers.
Age 10 days in refrigerator, then they are ready for eating.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in pan and pour off grease.
Add chopped onion, garlic, celery and green pepper to sausage and simmer until tender.
Wash rice and add to mixture in baking dish.
Stir in soups.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: dutch sauerkraut
directions: Slice bacon and fry until crisp.
Add onion and apple and cook until done.
Add sauerkraut; top with smoked sausage. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Prepare mashed potatoes.
Just before serving, drain liquid off sauerkraut mixture.
Remove sausage and add mashed potatoes to mixture.
Mix well and serve with sausage.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry party cake
directions: Cut
cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Crush 1 1/2 cups of the strawberries.
Add sugar to cream cheese, beating until smooth. Fold
in
whipped
topping.
Fold in crushed berries. Fill and frost cake.
Garnish with reserved berries.
Chill.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cover with 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover with lid and simmer for about 1 hour.
I usually double this recipe.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in blender and serve over tossed salad greens.
Can be stored indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Heat oil until hot and add flour; cook until light brown (peanut color).
Add all seasonings and cook until tender and then add puree, then water.
Cook 20 minutes (cook in Magnalite).
Stir with wooden spoon.
Do not cover it and don't let it boil.
Add crawfish; cook 10 to 15 minutes longer and add parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about an hour.
Test for doneness.

title: three-bean chili
directions: Heat oil in large Dutch oven.
Add beef, onion and garlic; cook over high heat, stirring to break up large pieces until beef loses its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and, stirring occasionally, simmer 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender and flavors have blended.

title: broccoli balls(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Cook broccoli with onions following package directions; drain. Mix entire contents of Stove Top ingredients with all (well). Make into balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix cornstarch and liquid in top of double boiler; heat over hot water until thick and clear.
Beat egg yolk until thick and lemon-colored; add hot liquid to egg.
Return to double boiler and cook until thick.
Cool.
Add to whipped cream.
Stir in drained fruit cocktail; put in freezing trays and freeze.
Cut 3 squares for each serving; serve on lettuce.

title: crawfish monica
directions: Saute the green onions in butter until soft.
Add cream and seasonings.
Bring to a boil and let simmer 5 to 8 minutes or until thickened.
Add crawfish tails and simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add cooked pasta and heat through.

title: scripture bars
directions: Note:
If any verse uses two or more foods, use the first one mentioned.
When you have found all the ingredients in the Bible reference, write them out and put them together.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Put dry ingredients together in bowl and mix with wire whip. Add to other ingredients you have mixed together.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Do not overbake.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt and mustard; add onion and small amount of vinegar.
Use mixer.
Add oil gradually, then remainder of vinegar.
Add celery seed last.
Beat until thick.
Makes one pint.
Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini stir-fry
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil.
Add the zucchini and sausage.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Put ingredients in a 2-quart dish or bean pot.
It may be topped with bacon strips, if desired.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli chicken rice
directions: In skillet, melt 1/2 cup margarine.
Add broccoli and onion. Saute in margarine.
Add cream of mushroom soup, Velveeta cheese and milk.
Blend well and remove from heat.
Cook rice.
Add all together.
Place in baking dish.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls; flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: onions sauteed with yogurt and sesame oil
directions: Heat in a large skillet the olive oil and onions.
Saute for 3 minutes, then reduce the heat to low.
Cook and cover for 5 minutes to "sweat" the onions down.
Remove the lid and finish sauteing the onions until tender.
Do not brown too much.
Stir in the yogurt and warm a minute until smooth.
Stir in parsley, sesame oil and salt and pepper to taste.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Boil the chicken with seasoning, using celery tops and parsley if you have some on hand.
Strain broth and use in preparing the cooked rice.
It adds flavor to your dish rather than using water. Mix all ingredients and place in buttered casserole or pan. Cover entire top with crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Make sauce with butter and cheese in microwave.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir.
Cook on low 5 to 6 hours.

title: rhubarb pie(deep dish)
directions: Put sliced rhubarb in a deep dish pie crust.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour over rhubarb.
Cook until set at 350°.
Cover with beaten egg whites.
Brown in oven.

title: instant relief fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan and set aside.
Melt butter and chocolate together over low heat in a heavy, medium-size pan. Stir in corn syrup, water and vanilla.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in sugar and nuts or marshmallows.
The mixture will be quite stiff.
Pack into prepared pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook until tender; drain.
Arrange a layer of squash in buttered casserole.
Add 1/2 can soup.
Add another layer of squash and remaining soup.
Mix bread crumbs in melted butter and arrange on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: parmesan crusted perch
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon cheese, low-fat yogurt, horseradish, mustard, lemon juice and margarine.
Spread evenly on one side of fillets.
Place fillets, coated side up, on a rack coated with cooking spray.
Place rack in broiler pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Broil 6-inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) 18 minutes or until golden and fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Yields 8 servings (127 calories, 2.4 g fat).

title: potato soup
directions: Add vegetables and ham to the chicken broth.
Add parsley flakes.
Cook until done.
Add 3 cups of milk, salt, pepper and all-purpose seasoning.
Thicken with a paste made with flour and milk; when adding thickening, do not have soup boiling.
Simmer.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, corn syrup and molasses. Mix dry ingredients.
Roll into small balls and roll in sugar. Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and peppers together.
Drain grease. Add soup, pizza sauce, oregano, Parmesan cheese and noodles to hamburger mixture.
Pour into 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch casserole dish.
Top with pepperoni slices.
Add Mozzarella cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox cake
directions: Follow directions on pudding box.
Line bottom of oblong pan with graham crackers.
Pour chocolate pudding onto lined graham crackers.
Put a layer of graham crackers on top of chocolate pudding.
Pour vanilla pudding onto graham crackers.
Crumble remaining crackers very fine.
Cover top of vanilla pudding.
Let set about 1 hour.
Decorate with cherries.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: new england salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in the order given.
Add oil gradually, stirring until well blended.
Remove garlic before serving.
Excellent on green salad, avocado and celery or thick slices of tomato.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring to a boil the first 6 ingredients and cool.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Blend in flour and vanilla; stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 8 servings.

title: date nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan sides and bottom.
Bring water to a boil in a small saucepan. Pour the water over the dates in a large mixing bowl.
Add the margarine and brown sugar; blend well.
Stir in the egg, butter and milk.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in mixing bowl.
Slowly stir in milk. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bread and vanilla.

title: german-italian beans
directions: Place sausages in skillet; brown on all sides.
Remove sausages from skillet.
Add onions and beans to pan drippings. Cook over moderate heat, stirring, until onions are transparent. Add basil, savory, salt, pepper, consomme, mushrooms and potatoes; mix well.
Return sausages to skillet.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 30 minutes, or until beans and potatoes are done.
Liquid can be thickened with cornstarch, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix well; pour on top of chicken ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 450°.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saut onions and celery in butter or oleo. Then add all other ingredients and place in 8 x 10 dish.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Beat egg whites with vinegar, vanilla and salt until soft peaks form.
Add sugar slowly.
Fold in pecans. Cover cookie sheets with brown paper.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 275° for 30 to 40 minutes until crisp and very slightly browned. Cool and remove from cookie sheets.
Yield:

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl; mix with spoon until all is mixed well.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan (no flour).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef & onions together until brown & cooked through, drain fat. Toss all ingredients together with Salad dressings.

title: mom's cutout cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together.
Add baking soda dissolved in hot water.
Stir in flour (may need to add rest with hands).
Roll dough in 4 balls, taking one ball at a time.
Roll into flat surface to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and fry potatoes in oil.
Remove and drain.
In skillet, pour out all oil except 2 to 3 tablespoons, enough to saute onion and pepper together.
Then, add potatoes and tomato. Stir well.
Cook until sauce is absorbed by potatoes.

title: pita crisps
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine the oil, cumin, cayenne pepper and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Split the pitas in half.
Brush the cut side of each half with flavored oil.
Stack the pitas and cut them in quarters.
Spread them on a baking sheet in a single layer and bake until golden brown, about 10 minutes.
Transfer to a rack and cool. Makes 32 Pita Crisps.

title: mama's mix
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine rice, tomato sauce, hamburger and green beans.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbling; serve.

title: red cabbage with raisins
directions: Combine all ingredients in large heavy skillet and cover. Simmer until cabbage is tender and most of the liquid has evaporated.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine cream cheese, bacon and pepper.
Cut stems off the mushrooms and fill with cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: special punch
directions: Mix sugar with 1 quart warm water to dissolve. Add the other 3 quarts water. Pour all juices in and mix. Add any color of food color of choice, if desired. Add sherbet in as you desire.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine sour cream, chili sauce, pickle relish, oil, green onions, celery and hard-cooked egg.
Stir with fork to blend. Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Stir again just before serving.
Makes 3 cups, 1 tablespoon has 15 calories and 1 gram fat.

title: lemon butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar, powdered sugar, butter and oil until light and fluffy.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice and egg; blend well.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 1 hour for easier handling.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add more juice, if needed, for a moist mixture.
Spoon onto split hamburger buns and serve hot.

title: diane's deer steak
directions: Season steaks with garlic powder and flour.
Brown in hot oil (enough oil to cover bottom of pan).
Place steaks in bottom of casserole dish; top with potatoes.
Add soup and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins. Stir in soda then cool. Combine sugar, butter and egg. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture. Stir in raisins and nuts. Pour into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix vegetables. Cover with water in soup pot; cook until tender. Mash as you desire with old-fashioned potato masher. Set aside.

title: chicken la broccoli
directions: Brown chicken breasts in frying pan.
Mix 1 can of broccoli soup with 1 can of milk.
Put in frying pan.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.

title: rolled out clusters
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in a saucepan.
Stir and bring to a boil, then boil one minute longer.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add oats and mix well.
Cool slightly and drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: hezzie vince egg custard
directions: Mix milk, sugar and butter in saucepan and cook on medium heat until hot, but not boiling.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour milk mixture over eggs, beating to mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Take out of oven before it gets done in the center as it will finish cooking while cooling.

title: crock-pot casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 6 hours on low.

title: quick vegetable beef soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef and sliced onion over moderate heat, stirring occasionally until beef is brown and onion tender (10 minutes).
Stir in broth, stewed tomatoes, mixed vegetables, corn and basil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; simmer until veggies are tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Contains 5 grams fat per serving.

title: mushroom florentine
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Line greased 9-inch square pan with spinach (defrosted and pressed dry).
Mix salt, butter and onion and sprinkle over spinach.
Sprinkle on 1/2 of the cheese, then add mushrooms.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and add second half of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn pones
directions: Combine the cornmeal and salt in a bowl.
Pour in the boiling water and beat until the mixture is smooth.
Shape the mixture into round balls and flatten into cakes about 1/2 inch thick. Lightly cover hot griddle with oil and cook corn pones until golden on each side.

title: patta
directions: Chop fine and saute onion, green pepper, garlic, tomato sauce and hamburger meat; drain very good (if you fry).
Mix flour, salt, Crisco, sugar and baking powder with 1/2 cup ice water (spoon and fork); knead it out and cut into little balls.
Flatten out; put meat mixture in center of dough pieces.
Fold over dough and press to seal edges.
Deep fry.

title: cream cheese crescent
directions: Combine butter and cheese until well blended.
Add flour and salt and shape into eight balls.
Wrap in plastic and chill 2 hours.
Roll each ball of dough into 8-inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over each wedge.
Roll wedges into crescents.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Dust warm cookies with powdered sugar.

title: mazettie
directions: Saute meats, onion, pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Add all ingredients except noodles and cheese.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Layer mixture with noodles and top with large portion of cheese.
Bake in covered casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350° in a 12 x 10 x 2-inch dish.
Uncover and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Shake meat tenderizer (thick) on both sides of a pot roast and place in refrigerator overnight.
Poke meat with fork after shaking on the tenderizer.

title: walnut applesauce fudge cake (rich & moist)
directions: Substitute applesauce for liquid called for on cake mix package and measure additional 1/4 c.
Mix cake as package directs, adding extra 1/4 c. applesauce in the first mixing.
Stir in walnuts and bake as per package instructions.

title: jellied salmon salad
directions: Dissolve the lemon jello in the boiling water.
When cool, add the vinegar and the salt.
As it begins to set, fold in the flaked salmon, the celery and the mayonnaise.
Chill until firm and serve on crisp lettuce.
May be garnished with more dressing, radish roses and paprika.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup milk.
Stir in nuts.
Put 1/2 mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Spread the other half of batter on top of the batter that was in the oven.
Bake for another 15 to 18 minutes.

title: buffet burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings; mix well.
Keeping meat mixture one inch from edges; press meat mixture into the bottom of a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes; drain.
Top mixture with cheese and bake 5 to 8 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven and allow to set (about 5 minutes).
Cut meat into 20 squares and place inside split rolls. Serve with mustard and mayonnaise.

title: banana cake
directions: In small bowl combine cake flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
In large bowl cream the butter and sugar, then add eggs.
In another small bowl measure 1 cup lightly mashed ripe bananas, vanilla and 1/4 cup yogurt.
(You can substitute buttermilk or sour cream for the yogurt; you may use flavored yogurt if you wish.)
Add the flour mixture alternately with the banana mixture into the butter mixture in thirds.
Bake in 2 round greased baking pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
A good use for overripe bananas.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening, salt and peanut butter; mix well.
Add both sugars gradually; cream thoroughly.
Add egg and milk, mixing well.
Drop from teaspoon onto sheets that are well-greased.
Dip a fork lightly in flour, then press down cookies flat, making crisscross top.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Cook macaroni.
Add to browned ground beef, sugar, pizza sauce, tomato sauce and tomato paste. Season with oregano, onion salt and garlic salt.
Add macaroni to meat mixture.
In casserole dish layer 1/2 meat mixture.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese; repeat.
Top with Parmesan cheese and pepperoni.
Put in microwave for 5 minutes or conventional oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix and let sit overnight to mingle the flavors.
Get a small loaf of dark bread from the bakery, unsliced.
Hollow out the center.
Cut the removed bread into small pieces.
Pour the dip into the hollowed out loaf and arrange the pieces of bread around the loaf.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain excess fat.
Add vegetable soup and water; season.
Cover mixture with biscuits.
Bake in oven at 400° until biscuits are golden brown.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except blueberries.
Then blend until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Bake in a greased tube pan that has been sprinkled with sugar, at 325° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli only slightly in boiling water.
In another pan, boil rice in 3 cups of water with salt.
When both are cooked, place in a large casserole dish and mix in scallions, cheese and soup.
Grate cheese on top and sprinkle bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly and light brown.

title: corn cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
When done, add Cheez Whiz, corn and soup.
Mix well and serve.

title: cherry streusel pie
directions: Drain 1/2 cup of thick sauce from pie filling and reserve.
To reserved sauce, mix in 1 tablespoon Amaretto and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract.
Set sauce aside.
Spoon cherries over bottom of pie shell.
Mix remaining 3 tablespoons Amaretto, egg, sour cream, sugar, vanilla, flour, remaining 1/4 teaspoon almond extract and salt.
Pour over cherries.
Bake in preheated 450° oven 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer.
Remove pie from oven.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer all ingredients (cold) in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Layer in large casserole dish in order listed.
Cover and bake at 350° until bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: death by chocolate
directions: In glass container, layer: 1/2 brownies (broken into chunks), 1/2 mousse, 1/2 candy bars and 1/2 topping, then again a layer of brownies, mousse, candy and topping. Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: delicious carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, vanilla, pineapple, carrots and pecans.
Add eggs last.
Pour into layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Frost.

title: secret recipe for green bean-rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook hamburger; drain.
In Pyrex or other baking casserole dish, mix soup, hamburger and rice.
Add salt and pepper as needed.
When mixed, then add green beans and mix carefully.
Prior to baking, pour enough water over mixture to more than cover it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: harrah's tahoe mud pie
directions: Blend with ice.
Put in chimney glass.
Garnish with tangled straw.

title: hamburger with potato casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until done.
Pour off excess fat.
Add cream of mushroom soup, undiluted.
In casserole dish, place half of hamburger mixture.
Add half of cheese.
Put rest of hamburger mixture and cheese in dish.
Cover with frozen French fries, Tater Tots or hash browns.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend for 60 seconds and serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Cream adding sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and extract.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Saute the onion in the butter.
Add the water and bouillon. Heat to boiling until dissolved.
Add the noodles and salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add the broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes.
Add the milk and cheese.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain.
Saute onion and 5 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add soup; mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer into ungreased baking dish.
Stir remaining butter and bread crumbs until lightly coated.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: deviled clams
directions: Chop clams and simmer in juice 5 minutes.
Saute celery leaves, green pepper and onion in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients.

title: crock-pot smothered steak
directions: Dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper.
Layer meat (floured), mushrooms and onion in crock-pot. Pour broth over all. Can add carrots and peeled potatoes on top, if desired. Cook in crock-pot on high 4 hours or slow (low) 8 to 10 hours.

title: christmas punch
directions: Place pineapple sherbet in punch bowl and cut into pieces. Pour cranberry juice over this.

title: apple cake
directions: Measure 1 3/4 cups apples into a big bowl; add sugar and let stand 10 minutes.
Sift flour; add next 5 ingredients.
Blend butter and egg into apple mixture.
Add flour and stir just until blended.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: red pickles
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over pickles.
Let stand overnight. Drain juice and heat again for 3 mornings.
Then put in jars and seal.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together; place half of mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk. Pour over warm cake. Sprinkle with nuts and chips. Spread
remaining cake batter over top with a large spoon. Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in an 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beet relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, set aside.
In large pan mix the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Add to the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil again.
Stir constantly.
Have jars and lids ready.
Boil jars and lids.
Pint jars are best.
Seal. Can be used as a nice compliment for holiday meals or anytime.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a hole in the middle of mixture. Add applesauce, eggs and oil.
Fold raisins and nuts into mixture. Pour mixture into a greased, lined tube pan and bake 45 minutes at 350° and 15 minutes at 375°.
When done, cover lightly until cool, preferably overnight.

title: date crinkles
directions: Combine
dates, sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Set aside to cool.

title: homemade sauerkraut
directions: *Will not get sour if too much salt is used.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup lemon juice and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Poke holes in warm cake and pour over.
This cake is for lemon lovers only.
Very lemony!

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk until mixture boils up.
Cool. Add confectioners sugar until desired consistency to spread.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients, except muffin mix.
Stir in muffin mix.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: laramie loaf
directions: Cut bread into top and bottom halves.
Combine cheddar cheese, cream cheese, olives, mayonaise, onion, mustard and worchestershire sauce.
Evenly spread 1/2 of the mixture on each half loaf.
Place 5 tomato slices on each, then crisscross bacon halves atop the tomatoes.
Wrap each loaf loosely in foil, leaving the top open. Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: blueberry biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients, adding blueberries last.
Stir until just blended.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Layer cooked noodles, tuna, peas and mushroom soup in casserole dish; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all together;
form into a log and roll in paprika.

title: smoked ham cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans. Make into ball. Roll in nuts.

title: fabienne's orange delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into ungreased pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli; use only the tops (flowerets).
Add crumbled, cooked bacon, chopped onions and raisins.
Mix dressing (mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and milk).
When ready to serve, add noodles and pour on dressing and mix.

title: ham and potato omelet(serves 6)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except paprika, in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until knife inserted in center comes out clean (40 to 45 minutes).

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix together soups, salsa and milk.
Cut up 4 tortillas at a time.
Layer tortillas, chicken and soup until all used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Mix the eggs, 2 teaspoons oil and the water.
Use this mixture to moisten dry chicken, then roll in cornstarch and fry in garlic and 1/2 cup oil until lightly browned.
Cover with Sweet and Sour Sauce.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes on each side.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt. Decrease baking soda to 1/4 teaspoon.
