title: braised pork loin
directions: Preheat a heavy pan (4-quart) on medium heat.
Pat pork loin dry and season with salt and pepper or Mrs. Dash.
Brown pork on all sides for 5 minutes.
Thinly slice onion and place in pan with roast.
Cover pan and reduce heat to medium low.
After 30 minutes, turn pork and add 1/2 to 1 cup water.
Turn roast occasionally and cook for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: batter-up beef pie
directions: Combine beef, onions, carrots, potatoes and gravy; set aside. Melt butter in bottom of 8-inch square baking dish in oven. Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir until blended and pour into baking dish.
Pour beef mixture over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake and serve.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Save in a separate bowl 1/4 package of dressing mix.
Mix 3/4 package remaining with melted oleo.
Add squash, onion, carrots, soup and sour cream.
Place in baking dish and top with dressing mix saved in bowl.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix other ingredients to beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until pie doesn't shake in center.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy pan, cook the first 5 ingredients until hard crack stage on thermometer (295°).
Remove from heat and add the soda. Stir vigorously.
Put into well-greased pan, spreading thin. When cool, crack into pieces.

title: triple bean chowder
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until soft.
Stir in flour, sauce and all seasonings until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute.
Add beans.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Serve with biscuits.

title: stewed carrots and apples
directions: Place carrots in medium saucepan; cover with water.
Boil until just tender (about 10 minutes).
Add apples, sugar and cinnamon; boil until apples are soft (5 to 10 minutes).
Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water.
Slowly add to pan until sauce is thickened.

title: corned beef or venison
directions: Combine last 6 ingredients and then add saltpeter mixture.
Put meat in container (crock or slow cooker).
Pour marinade over meat. Weight down with plate.
Leave for 3 weeks.
Turn occasionally.
If meat is bloody, rinse and then cook as a regular roast.
Serve warm or cold.
Delicious!

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine warm water and yeast; add milk, sugar, salt, eggs and shortening.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth.
Let rise until double. Shape into rolls.
Place into greased pans; let rise again.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Mix together.
Crush 1 roll Ritz crackers and spread over vegetables.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly all over, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: thick juicy hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into 6 or 8 equal patties. Grill or broil in oven until brown.

title: crab-stuffed chicken
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter, add flour until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Combine milk, broth and wine; gradually add to flour mixture.
Cook until thickened and bubbly, set aside.
Saute green onions in 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in crabmeat, mushrooms, cracker crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper and 2 tablespoons of sauce.
Flatten chicken breasts.
Spoon 1/4 cup crabmeat mixture in center of breasts; fold sides in; place seam side down in greased baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over breasts.
Cover, bake 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika; bake additional time for cheese to melt.

title: dirt
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 2/3 of the Oreo cookies. Smooth to make layer even.
In large bowl mix until smooth the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and set it aside.
In another bowl prepare pudding, using milk.
Add both mixtures together, stirring until well blended.
Pour over the layer of crushed cookies.
Sprinkle with remaining Oreo cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: sherried spareribs
directions: Place ribs on a lightly greased rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.
In a medium saucepan, saute onion in oil.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to sauteed onion.
Bring to a boil, stirring well.
Place roasting pan 7 to 8-inches from heating element.
Broil ribs 15 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.
Baste liberally with sauce. Serve remaining sauce with spareribs.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: About 1 hour before serving:

title: quick cheeseburger pie
directions: Prebake pie crust at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cook and stir beef, onion and garlic in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain. Sprinkle with salt and flour.
Stir in pickle juice, milk, pickles and 1 cup of cheese.
Spoon into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes; sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until crust is golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and shortening with sugars and vanilla. Beat in eggs and cinnamon. Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: glazed carrot coins
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in a small amount of water until crisp-tender; drain.
Remove and keep warm.
In the same pan, heat brown sugar and butter until bubbly.
Stir in lemon peel.
Return carrots to pan; cook and stir over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until glazed.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pina colada squares
directions: In medium bowl, mix unflavored gelatin with Sweet 'N Low.
Add hot juice and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch baking pan and chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 6 dozen squares.

title: wassail
directions: Bring the apple juice, spice bag and brown sugar to a boil; stir in orange juice and lemonade.
Remove spice bag.
Turn heat down to low or put in a coffeepot.

title: corn salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine vegetables.
Pour in dressing.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: grandmother jones' raw apple cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts, dates and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan.
Let stand a little before cutting.
Serve hot with whipped cream.

title: gourmet meatballs
directions: Grate onion; add egg and stir.
Add meat and seasonings; mix well.
Make small meatballs about the size of marbles.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain liquid from vegetables.
Combine last four ingredients in pan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let marinate, covered, 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: grayce's cheese ball
directions: Let all ingredients stand to room temperature.
Mix thoroughly; form into ball.
Chill slightly and roll in nuts.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Grease a 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Into medium-size mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, and mace.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Blend together eggs, sweet potato, milk and shortening.
Add liquid all at once to flour mixture, stirring until blended.
Turn into pan.
Press pecan halves over top of batter to form design.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: edna butler's green tomato catsup
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
In separate container, combine sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour vinegar mixture over cut up vegetables.
Heat to boiling (do not overcook).
Put in clean jars and seal.
Can just cold pack and can in the pressure canner at 5 pounds pressure for 5 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Bring tomatoes, broth and water to a boil.
Add the rest of ingredients, bring back to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: joe's ribs
directions: Season ribs with the garlic, paprika and seasoned salt.
Put the ribs on a rack in a pan lined with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes per side.
When done, let cool on rack. Place in refrigerator all day or overnight for better flavor.

title: jody's favorite fresh peach pie
directions: Make a crust, uncooked.
Fill 2/3 full of sliced, fresh peaches.
Beat eggs with fork and add flour and sugar.
Add melted butter. Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave for 45 minutes.

title: wicked fudge nut pie
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups nuts.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, stir sweetened condensed milk, margarine and cocoa until margarine melts and mixture is warm.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, flour, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into prepared crust. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes until center is firm.
Serve warm or cold, garnished with whipped cream and remaining nuts.

title: turtle pecan cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine cookie crumbs and butter.
Press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat the cream cheese in a large bowl until creamy.
Add sugar, flour, salt and vanilla. Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in cream.
Pour over crust.
Bake 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 200°; continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Loosen cake from the rim of pan.
Cool before removing rim of pan.
Drizzle with Caramel Topping and Chocolate Topping.
Refrigerate.
Sprinkle with pecans just before serving.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix 1/4 stick melted margarine with the Ritz crackers.

title: hershey chocolate pie
directions: Melt candy bar over low heat.
Let cool slightly.
Mix into Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Add salt and milk and boil, stirring.
Add sugar, then boil gently for 15 minutes. Great warm on ice cream!

title: hardtack candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan; stir until dissolved.
Cover and cook over high heat until boiling.
Remove cover; lower heat to medium.
Continue to cook to hard crack stage (300° to 310°).
Remove from heat and add flavoring and food coloring.
Stir to mix.

title: no peak! chicken
directions: Add soups, rice and water in baking dish.
Stir and add chicken parts or boneless chicken breasts.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
No stirring is necessary.

title: mama's coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 250 degrees for 15 minutes and 300 degrees for 30 minutes. Makes two pies.

title: green christmas salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on package and cool until partially set.
Add grated cheese, marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Add whipped cream and chill until set.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Combine flour, butter and half of the pecans in the bottom of a buttered pan (9 x 12-inch) and bake until lightly browned.
When cool, cover with pudding (made with pie recipe).
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle top with remaining pecans.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients. Fry in hot oil until brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels.

title: favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream the Crisco, sugars and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend in the egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda in a sifter.
Sift together into creamed mixture, gradually. Stir in chocolate chips.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute all vegetables in oil until soft.
Add garlic; cook 5 more minutes.
Deglaze with red wine.
Add tomato paste; reduce heat to low.
Cook until vegetables are very soft.
Stir in fresh oregano, salt and pepper.

title: delicious dainties
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift cream of tartar with flour.
Mix gradually.
Chill.
Roll, cut and bake.

title: candy pastel patties
directions: Beat 1/3 cup Karo light corn syrup, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Mix in confectioners sugar and coloring.
Knead mixture until smooth.
You may want to keep your hands dusted with confectioners sugar as you knead.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch patties. Press top of patties with a fork then top with a walnut half.

title: yule log
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Grease raisins and they will not go to the bottom.

title: delux potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion, parsley, salt and pepper with bouillon cubes in water until tender.
Add cheese, milk and flour and cook until thick.

title: mother's christmas fruitcake
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 3 tablespoons juice. Cut cherries in half; set aside. Drain prunes, reserving 6 tablespoons syrup; pit prunes and set aside. Cream sugar, shortening and eggs at medium speed of a mixer for 2 minutes or until smooth. Stir in cherries, reserved cherry juice, prunes, reserved prune syrup, walnuts and next 3 ingredients. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; add to creamed mixture and stir well. Spoon batter into a 10-inch tube pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pan 10 minutes on a wire rack; remove from pan and let cool completely. Store tightly wrapped in heavy-duty plastic wrap. Yield: 32 servings (serving size: one 3/4-inch slice).

title: fish ragout
directions: If fish is frozen, thaw enough to cut into 1-inch cubes or cut fresh fish into cubes; set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients together well and put into 4 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: good potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fudge jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and spray a 9 x 13-inch oblong glass baking dish with Pam.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Cut meat into thin strips.
Brown meat with onion mixture.
Add soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Blend in sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Season to taste.
Serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: cheese strata
directions: Mix mustard and butter and spread on bread.
Cut bread into piece to fit into a greased baking dish.
Slice cheese into thin slices.
Put bread and cheese in alternate layers into baking dish, ending with cheese on top layer.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and paprika.
Beat eggs.
Combine with milk; pour over bread and cheese.
Cut the partially cooked bacon (to eliminate extra grease) into 2-inch slices and lay on top.

title: oatmeal chews
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine brown sugar and margarine.
Cook and stir until margarine is melted.
Stir in oats, baking powder and cinnamon; mix well.
Spread mixture in a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 18 minutes, or until golden.
(Center will be soft.)
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 24.

title: chipped ham sandwich
directions: Saute chipped ham in oleo.
Add barbecue sauce to ham and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve in fresh bun with pickles.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks and put in dry ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water.
In a separate pan, melt butter then add flour stiring until smooth.
Add milk, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: lumpia
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain off all liquid.
Mix other ingredients and simmer until meat is well done.
Put one tablespoon mix in center of lumpia wrapper.
Roll and fold in edges.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup orange juice with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Blend at lowest speed of mixer for 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Drizzle remaining orange juice over warm cake and sprinkle with Topping.

title: linguini and clam sauce
directions: Slowly brown garlic in olive oil.
Add clam juice and parsley; simmer 30 minutes.
Add clams and heat 10 minutes.
Serve with linguini or other pasta and Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook zucchinis in boiling salted water for 10-15 minutes. In the meantime saute onion and garlic in 3 tbsp butter. Add stewed tomatoes, saltines, salt and pepper, Italian seasoning, and bacon.

title: angel fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until forms a hard ball.
Beat egg whites. Add to hot mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: pork pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cook ground beef and pork with onion.
Add some water to make some juice.
Add spices and then potatoes to absorb juice.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and pour into casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wheaties cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder and add.
Add vanilla.
Add Wheaties, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, no longer.
This makes a large amount.
Roll in balls the size of a quarter and place on greased cookie sheet.
Dough will be stiff.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla at medium speed until light (about one minute).
Add melted margarine and blend thoroughly. Mix in flour and cocoa at low speed.
Add nuts and/or coconut if desired.

Stir in and spread evenly in greased 8-inch square pan. Microwave on High for 6 or 7 minutes, rotating every two minutes. Top looks dry and will spring back when lightly touched if done. Best eaten warm.

title: marinated brisket
directions: Combine the above ingredients except for the barbecue sauce. Brush on brisket.
Wrap meat tightly in foil and marinate in refrigerator overnight. Before cooking, open the foil and pour 1 cup of barbecue sauce over the meat, then re-seal. Bake for 3 hours at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil, apple vinegar, salt and dry mustard to a boil.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a large microwavable bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
When through, stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: yum-yums
directions: Melt margarine; add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix. Add following and stir after each:
chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, pecans, coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Place in greased 13-inch pan and cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: savory beans and tomatoes
directions: Steam beans until tender. Rinse in cold water and drain.
Cut tomatoes into thin wedges; set aside.

title: quiche-like pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Mix carrots, rice, cheese, onions and basil; spread in a plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in a blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a greased 9x13 pan for baking.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef and sausage, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape firmly into loaf (8 x 4-inch).
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes. In a saucepan, blend remaining soup, water and 3 to 4 tablespoons dripping from pan.
Heat and stir occasionally.
Serve on top of meat loaf.

title: pull-apart parmesan garlic bubble loaf
directions: Cut dough in 16 equal pieces.
Shape in balls.
Place on floured surface; cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Stir Parmesan and garlic powder into melted butter.
Using spoon, roll balls in butter mixture.
In greased 8-inch layer cake pan or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, arrange balls loosely in 2 layers.
Let rise in warm draft free place until doubled.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; cook broccoli.
Mix everything together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and add taco seasoning and water.
Put in large bowl.
Add everything but lettuce and chips.
Mix well and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Before serving, add lettuce and chips.

title: honey cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour and all dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until thick and light in color.
Beat in oil, honey and coffee.
Stir in flour mixture and nuts.
Oil two 9-inch loaf pans and line with foil. Pour mixture into pans and bake at 325° for 50 minutes until browned and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on a rack before removing from pans.

title: peanut brittle with chocolate chips
directions: Blend all ingredients together and press in a greased and floured baking pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 c. of peanuts on top and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple evenly in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over fruit and place pats of butter or margarine over top, using whole stick. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, being careful not to overbake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice chicken and bread.
Add chicken noodle soup and cream of chicken soup.
Don't dilute soups.
Mix in egg and melted margarine.
Place in greased baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: 7 in 1 bar
directions: Mix crackers and margarine together.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and walnuts on top.
Pour one can condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa and milk together 1 minute.
Stir.
Add oatmeal, vanilla, margarine and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool until firm.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine.
Spread into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake it at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool. Mix powdered sugar, half topping and cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding according to package directions.
Spread over cheese layer.
Spread remaining topping over pudding layer.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: wassail
directions: Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, whole spice and juice into cider. Take apple, wash and core (but not clear through). Pack full of brown sugar. Half-inch down, cut strip of peeling off apple and put whole cloves around the apple. Bake apple at 350° for 15 minutes in a dish of water. Put cider mixture in crock-pot. Put apple in when warm to float around and flavor. Keep warm.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix crushed Oreos with 1 stick melted margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let ice cream get very soft and spread on top of Oreos.
Put in freezer.
Put chocolate, 1 stick margarine, salt, 2/3 cup sugar, milk and vanilla in a pot on the stove; melt and cook until thick, about 4 or 5 minutes, stirring fairly constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; let cool and then pour over ice cream from freezer.
Return to freezer and serve whenever you wish.
When you cover it, be sure the foil is not on chocolate as it will stick to it.
If you have a pan with a cover, this works best.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Chop sausage into bite-sized rounds.
Combine all ingredients. Bake in large, greased casserole dish for one hour, covered, or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomatoes, tomato soup and beans.
Bring to boil.
Add small head chopped cabbage, chili powder and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pickle okra
directions: Select small size okra; wash well, leaving small end of stem on.
Pack okra in clean sterilized jars.
Put a head of dill or dill seed with a bud of garlic in each jar.
Make brine of vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil and pour over okra.
Seal.
Let set for 4 or 6 weeks.
Be sure no dill seeds are under lid when you seal it, or it will spoil.

title: charleston cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, grated cheese, green onion, and mayonnaise. Spread in flat dish (9x9).
Crush "6" Ritz crackers & crush very fine & sprinkle over the top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-15 minutes until melted.
Microwave bacon & crumble.
Take cheese mixture out of oven & sprinkle bacon on top. Serve hot with ritz crackers.

title: mediterranean casserole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in butter until soft.
Add meat.
Cook until brown.
Stir occasionally.
Blend in soup and catsup. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, on low heat for 8 minutes, stirring several times.
Blend cream cheese, milk, lemon juice, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with noodles in baking dish. Pour some meat mixture over all. Alternate with noodles and mixture again.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place dried beef on chicken and roll up.
Wrap bacon around outside of chicken and secure with a toothpick.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Uncover the last 30 minutes to brown on top.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Set pineapple chunks and juice aside.
Cut pork into 1/2-inch cubes. Set aside.
Combine reserved pineapple juice and cornstarch; stir in chicken broth, red wine vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce; set aside.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Blend oleo and flour.
Sprinkle the three ingredients, well mixed, over the fruit which has been placed in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top is brown.

title: oven-fried catfish(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place bread cubes in a food processor and process 30 seconds or until breadcrumbs are fine. Sprinkle breadcrumbs onto a baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until lightly browned. Place breadcrumbs in a shallow dish; set aside. Increase oven temperature to 450°.

title: aunt von's jello
directions: Mix 1 box of Jell-O, 1 can crushed pineapple (drained), frozen strawberries (drained), 3 mashed bananas and 1 cup chopped pecans. Let gel in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When gelled, spread sour cream over Jell-O.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour on top of gelled Jell-O. Let this gel.
Keep refrigerated.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except milk and butter.
Add butter to milk and heat so that butter melts.
Add to corn mixture.
Pour into a greased 1 quart casserole.
Bake one hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken. Brown in oleo or butter.
Saute the onion and pepper in oleo after removing chicken.
Crush bouillon cubes with fork. Add to onion and pepper.
Stir in rice. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 1/2 cups water.
Place in baking pan. Lay chicken on top of rice. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour evenly over biscuits. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: kahlua pecan fudge pie
directions: Prepare
9-inch
pie
shell.
Turn chocolate into small saucepan.
Add
Kahlua and place over low heat until chocolate melts,
stirring
smooth.
Hand
beat
eggs
lightly.
Stir in brown
sugar, salt, vanilla, corn syrup and chocolate mixture. Then stir
in butter and 1 cup of pecans.
Turn into pie shell and sprinkle
remaining 1/2 cup pecans on top.
Bake slightly below center of moderate 350° oven until barely set in center and pastry
is	light golden brown, 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Cut into small wedges and serve with Kahlua Cream. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked kielbasa
directions: Boil kielbasa 1/2 hour in water.
Pour off water.
Add kielbasa to mixture and bake 1 hour at 250° with lid.

title: hobo bread
directions: Boil raisins in hot water; let stand and cool.
Add soda to raisins; stir.
Blend in sugar and oil.
Add egg.
Mix in flour. Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: fudge brownie fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and stir.
Add melted butter and chocolate.
Mix flour, salt and chopped nuts; add.
Add vanilla and stir; do not beat.
Pour in a buttered 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool, cut and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into square pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook beef first.
Add as many onions, carrots, corn, green beans, and peas as you like, plus 10 potatoes, and brown gravy mix.
(Thicken the gravy mix with corn starch or flour.)
Cook all together.

title: aunt mary's dressing
directions: Stir ingredients well and let stand a while to absorb flavors.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Melt butter and blend in sugar.
Mix in beaten eggs and mashed bananas, blending until smooth.
Sift all-purpose flour with salt and soda.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Add dry ingredients alternately with hot water.
Stir in chopped nut meats.
Turn into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: eggplant and okra
directions: Combine eggplant, onion, tomatoes and okra; season with salt and pepper.
Cook 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt and flavoring.
Mix good, then add milk, oil and flour.
Mix until smooth.
Make 10 layers. Use 3 tablespoons in each cake pan.
Put wax paper in bottom of pans, then spray with Pam before adding batter.
Bake at 350° until layers are done (do not brown).

title: shirley's lasagna
directions: Brown beef and garlic; add tomato paste, tomatoes and spices and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook the lasagna noodles, adding one tablespoon of oil to the water.
When cooked, drain the lasagna. Layer in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, starting with the sauce and ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let sit for 15 minutes before serving.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Add flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans. Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Pour sauce over cake while it is still warm.

title: pancake sauce
directions: Mix butter until fluffy.
Add brown sugar, mixing well.
Add pecans.
Spread on hot pancakes.

title: ranger cookies(3 to 4 dozen)
directions: Mix together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oatmeal, nuts and dates.
After smooth, add Rice Krispies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together the chicken, onions, mushrooms and 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese.
Dip tortillas in oil or you can dip them in enchilada sauce.
Fill shells and roll up.
Place, seam side down, in greased casserole dish.
Mix together the sour cream, cream of chicken soup and 1/2 soup can of water.
Pour this mixture over the enchiladas and top with the remaining cheese.
You can add green chilies on top of the cheese.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients well like pastry.
Add milk to moisten. Roll into small balls.
Cook at 350° near the top of the oven for about 15 to 18 minutes on a cookie sheet.
These can be frozen and reheated in 300° oven for 10 minutes or you can microwave.

title: coconut lemon freeze
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Beat egg yolks in large bowl until thick.
Stir in milk, lemon juice and rind until well blended.
Fold in 1 2/3 cups of coconut and whipped topping.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Spoon over crumb crust.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 9 servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 8x9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes

title: ham balls
directions: Combine all ingredients. Roll into nickel size balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and water in a pan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add orange jello and cream cheese.
Chill until set.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry hamburger. Before it loses pink color, add onions and pepper. Continue frying until done. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, Italian seasoning, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: naughty hula pie
directions: Mix butter, chocolate wafers and sugar.
Press into the bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream shortening, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cake may be served plain, iced or with whipped topping.

title: hearty noodles
directions: Cook wide noodles.
Melt butter in a large, preheated skillet. Saute zucchini, bell pepper and garlic for 4 minutes.
Next, add cream, salt and pepper.
Simmer lightly to a medium thin consistency.
When noodles are done, add cream sauce; mix well and toss in bacon.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: popover pizza
directions: Pour this mixture over the pizza mix and bake until done.

title: banana yogurt flip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor container. Blend on high speed about 1 minute or until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix well all ingredients except the cheese and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, for 50 minutes at 325°. Spread the cheese over the casserole and bake another 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let sit for a few minutes before serving.

title: broccoli brag
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and pour into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour. Cut into squares.

title: woodward house tea cakes
directions: Mix butter with hands; add sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and blend; add another cup flour.
Work until stiff.
Add to 11 x 8-inch pan, ungreased.
Press flat and fork over all of it (you can use a Springerle pin and roll out first).
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut immediately into small squares.
Do not brown!

title: ladyfinger balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and let chill about 2 or 3 hours. Shape into balls, put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 18 minutes or until they get light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar after they have cooled.
Store in covered tin or airtight container.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix and add to very hard white sauce.
Roll in cakes and dip in egg and cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, water, cheese and butter.
Put cooked rice in bottom of casserole dish, 9 x 11-inch.
Place broccoli on top of rice, then pour soup mixture over broccoli.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Turn into buttered dish (9 x 13-inch).
Top with 1/2 pound chopped, uncooked bacon and 1/4 cup chopped stuffed olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Cover each filet with mayonnaise and roll in bread crumbs. Place filets on greased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 20 minutes, 10 minutes on each side.

title: chocolate angel cake dessert
directions: Melt chocolate with sugar over hot water.
Remove from heat; add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Cool 5 minutes.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Break angel food cake into bits; sprinkle layer into bottom of buttered 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan, using 1/2 chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle nut meats over cake; cover with chocolate mixture.
Dot with rest of cake and nuts.
Then cover with rest of chocolate mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Chop up nuts; add to cake mix.
Pour cherry pie filling in pan.
Pour cake and nut mixture over filling.
Place pats of margarine on top; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: modeling clay
directions: Mix, adding water to desired consistency.
Can be stored in plastic for several days.

title: petite brioches
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water and let stand to soften.
Add hot milk to butter, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 1/2 cup flour.
Add softened yeast and mix well.
Beat in 1 1/2 cups flour. Add eggs and 4 yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in enough of the remaining flour to make soft dough.
Beat for at least 5 minutes.
Turn into large greased bowl and brush with melted butter (not hot).
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch in.
Brush again with melted butter.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours or overnight.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Shape 2/3 of dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place into small greased brioche pans or two-inch muffin pans.
Shape equal number of small balls from remaining dough.
Roll each into a cone shape.
Make a shallow dent in center of each large ball; insert tips of cones.
Cover with a towel.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Combine remaining egg yolk and 1 tablespoon milk.
Brush over surface of rolls.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.
Are feather light and hat shape.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as box directed, only use chicken broth as part of liquid.
Layer 1/2 can of each soup on bottom of casserole dish.
Place a layer of chicken over soup.
Spread sour cream over it.
Add 1/2 of dressing.
Repeat layer, ending with dressing. Bake at 375° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: spectacular spinach
directions: Cook spinach in unsalted water and drain.
Blend soup mix and sour cream.
Add spinach.
Place in casserole.
Top with onion rings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a square pan at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour an 18 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Pillsbury Plus yellow cake mix.
Bake 20 minutes. While cake is baking, mix flour, sugar and cinnamon well.
Add vanilla and softened butter.
(Use fingers or fork.)
Sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Cool.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top.

title: chicken nacho casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole dish in this order:
Chips, chicken, soups and Velveeta slices.
Repeat and top with cheese. Warm in oven just long enough to melt cheese.
Sop up with flour tortillas!

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water. Let cool. Add 2/3 cup peach juice. Refrigerate until slightly set. Mix in almond extract, Cool Whip and pureed peaches. Put in mold and refrigerate until set.

title: hot tomato relish
directions: I use a small canner that holds 5 quart-size jars.
Cook ingredients down until thick, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Put into pint-size canning jars.

title: oriental beef and tomato
directions: Make marinade of first 6 ingredients.
Place meat in shallow dish and marinate for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare vegetables. In large skillet or wok, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Remove meat from marinade and place in skillet, quickly stirring and fry until desired doneness.
Remove from heat and place meat onto plate.
In same skillet, add 2 tablespoons oil.
Add celery, onion and pepper; saute until tender-crisp.
Remove steak to skillet and reserved marinade.
Stir cornstarch into broth and add to skillet. Stir until thickens.
Stir in tomatoes, water chestnuts and bean sprouts.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine and blend all ingredients.
Chill.
Makes a very large amount.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine with sugar over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from stove and add well beaten eggs.
Add coconut, raisins and nuts.
Stir in vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: caramel pecan cheese layer pie
directions: Place all ingredients (except nuts) into mixer bowl and beat until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and top with nuts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in well greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until set or until knife comes out clean.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut warm, cooked potatoes in cubes.
Set aside.
Cook diced bacon until crisp.
Drain, but save 1 tablespoon fat.
Cook onion in this.
When onion is tender, add the paste (water, vinegar, sugar, flour and salt) and cook until this is thick.
Add drained bacon and pour over potatoes.
Toss to coat.
Serve warm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots and cook in salted water until tender. Drain well.
Chop pepper and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over carrots while still hot.
Marinate 2 or 3 days in refrigerator.
Drain before serving or save broth or liquid because this will last several days.

title: never fail brownies(easy and so good!)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 15-inch pan.
Melt margarine in medium saucepan. In the same pan, add sugar and eggs. Mix well. Stir in flour and cocoa.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: enchilada suiza
directions: Mix first four ingredients and set aside.
Cut up chicken in small pieces and grill.
Combine cooked chicken, green onions and olives.
Fill tortilla with meat mixture and Monterey Jack cheese and roll.
Cover enchiladas with soup mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zesty italian chicken
directions: Cut skin off chicken and rinse.
Dip chicken into egg.
Then roll chicken in corn flake crumbs.
Place chicken in single layer on baking dish.
Shake dressing well.
Pour 2 or 3 tablespoons of dressing on each piece of chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes, until chicken is brown.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread out the crescent dinner rolls onto a cookie sheet (cover the baking sheet).
Bake according to the package directions.
Let cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco oil and sugar; add eggs and salt and mix well. Add flour and soda combined with buttermilk alternately.
Add mashed bananas.
Fold in nuts.
Grease 2 regular size loaf pans; pour in mixture and bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
When bread leaves sides of pan and toothpick comes out clean, bread is done.
This recipe can be doubled.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: cream pineapple squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter and press in well-greased pan, 9 x 9-inches.
Cream butter and confectioners sugar; add eggs and beat until creamy.
Spread over crumb mixture. Fold pineapple in whipped cream; spread over sugar mixture. Sprinkle with crumbs.

title: corn pone(a favorite recipe from my grandmother, emma mitchell)
directions: Butter a square pan or an iron skillet.
Mix cornmeal sugar and salt together.
Cut butter into 4 to 5 pieces and add to dry mixture.
Slowly pour 1 cup of boiling water over the dry mixture, stirring very slowly.
Add the second cup of water and let it cook the dry mixture as you stir slowly.
Pour the third cup over the same way.

title: spiral pasta salad
directions: Place pasta and vegetables in large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over pasta, toss to coat. Chill 30 minutes.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles as label directs; drain.
Meanwhile on waxed paper, combine bread crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
In small dish, with fork, beat eggs with 2 tablespoons water.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture, then crumb mixture.
In large skillet over medium heat, in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook eggplant slices, a few at a time until tender, adding more oil when necessary.
Drain on paper towels.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In pan, layer half of noodles, eggplant slices, Mozzarella and spaghetti sauce; repeat.
Evenly sprinkle Parmesan cheese over sauce.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown ground beef in oil; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and sugar.
Separate biscuits and place in each muffin pan hole. Press against bottom and sides to form cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: spicy sweet potato wedges
directions: Heat oven to 475°. Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch wide wedges. Toss with vegetable oil, sugar, chili powder and salt. Spread on a greased baking sheet. Roast 15 to 20 minutes, shaking them once during cooking. Take out of oven and drizzle with maple syrup mixed with cider vinegar.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken and rice; drain vegetables. Mix and bake until bubbly at 350°. Enjoy!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place
peaches	on
bottom
of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place dry cake mix on top of peaches.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet milkshake(vanilla)
directions: Using a blender, pour in milk and ice cubes.
Add Sweet 'N Low and vanilla.
Process for 1 to 2 minutes or until mixed well.
You can add a little chocolate syrup or banana but you are also adding calories.
(I do not like Sweet 'N Low or vanilla milkshakes, but these are delicious and satisfy the cravings of sweets without the extra calories.)

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients mixing well.
Use about 1/2 c. cheese for top and bottom of batter and about 1/2 c. in mix with other ingredients.
Pour batter in well oiled 8 or 9 inch iron skillet. Bake at 425 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: granny's sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 16 to 18 muffin tins.
Combine dry ingredients; add egg, milk, oil and sweet potato.
Mix and fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake approximately 20 minutes or until the center springs back when touched lightly.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grind cheese and nuts through food grinder.
Have cream cheese soft.
Mash garlic clove and add.
Mix all together until thoroughly blended.
Make 2 rolls about the size of a silver dollar in diameter.
Roll the rolls in chili powder sprinkled on waxed paper.
The amount of chili powder can be varied.
Where rolls are well covered, place in refrigerator to harden.
Cut in thin slices and serve on crackers.

title: two-tone fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk, soft margarine and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add marshmallows.
Mix until marshmallows melt and mixture is smooth.
Place half the hot mixture in a bowl. Add butterscotch morsels, chopped nuts and maple extract. Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Set aside.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter until creamy; gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs; add flour and other ingredients.
Also, add oat mixture.
Mix well and pour batter into well greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.

title: stuffed banana peppers
directions: Soak peppers in salt water after removing seeds.
Prepare filling all ingredients together.
Stuff peppers and pack in jars with sprig of fresh dill and small amount of garlic in the bottom of jars or 1 teaspoon dill seed.

title: lemon cream
directions: Chill all ingredients until half set.
Fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
Pour into a greased mold. Unmold when set and surround with strawberries.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together in large bowl and shape into small meatballs and place into a pan in one layer, side by side.
Do not cook.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Stir together thoroughly in a bowl of loyalty.
Stir in equal amounts of work and play.
Add one cup of faith, one cup of hope and one cup of Christianity.
Add a teaspoon of great songs. Season to taste with culture and generous amount of worship. Place in a good-natured pan, well-greased with security.
Sprinkle lightly with tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a well-tempered oven.
When done, remove and top with a thick coating of Christianity and teachings.
Garnish with a sense of humor and some smiles.
Serve rapidly.

title: corn pudding(serves 8)
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Beat eggs.
Add corn, sugar, flour, cayenne and salt.
Stir.
Add scalded milk.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cook 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
After 15 to 20 minutes, stir and return to oven.

title: dutch apies cakes(pennsylvania dutch recipe)
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and baking soda. Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender.
Mix in the sour cream.
Roll out the dough about 1/8-inch thick on a floured surface and cut into 2-inch rounds or squares. Transfer to a cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa together. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Boil noodles.
Brown hamburger.
Add all other ingredients into hamburger, except cheese.
Allow to simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Layer noodles, sauce and the cheese of your choice. Bake in oven until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: divinity
directions: In a 3-quart casserole dish, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Cook on High for 5 minutes; stir.
Cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes, or until a hard ball forms in water.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks; pour over syrup mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla; fold in.
Spoon onto wax paper; let dry.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, sugar and salt. Add the diced bananas to the dry ingredients along with the oil, crushed pineapple with its juice, vanilla and eggs.
Stir to blend, but do not beat.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done. When cooled, remove and drizzle with Butter Rum Icing or frost as desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and milk. Cook until soft ball forms in cold water (234°). Remove from heat. Quickly add peanut butter, butter, chocolate chips and vanilla. Blend well. Pour into 9 x 9 x 2 buttered pan. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix 1 cup plain flour with pecans, cherries, pineapple and dates.
Combine all ingredients together.
Spoon drop cookies. Cook at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients and cook at 350° for 65 minutes or until done.

title: tacos
directions: Cook hamburger meat until done.
Put in seasoning.
Warm taco shells.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, sugar, flour, butter, salt, both extracts and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 10 minutes at 375° and then 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from heat, cool on rack until set then refrigerate until serving.

title: crab mousse
directions: Mix gelatine and water in a small bowl.
Heat soup until warm. Add cream cheese, gelatine, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour into mold, sprayed with Pam.
Chill until served.

title: pea casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 of the onion rings.
Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle reserved onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and onions
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until golden, about 7 minutes. Add mushrooms and cook until softened (3 minutes). Rinse rice in strainer under cold running water.
Add rice, water, salt and pepper to onion mixture. Stir well. Cook, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes or until rice is tender.
Be sure it doesn't get mushy.
Drain excess liquid and fluff rice with fork.

title: kitchen sausage salami
directions: Mix spices together.
Sprinkle on meat.
Mix well.
Cover. Refrigerate.
Knead once a day for 3 days.
On the fourth day, make 3 rolls.
Bake on broiler pan so fat will drain.
Bake at 150° for 11 hours, uncovered.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put milk in double boiler.
Separate egg yolks from whites. Whip yolks and add flour.
Mix well and add to milk along with sugar, salt and coconut.
Let cook until done; stir in flavoring. Beat egg whites until frothy, then add three tablespoons of sugar, stirring well.
Spread evenly over your pie.
Sprinkle coconut over the top and put in oven to brown.

title: grandmother's rice
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Will be golden brown on top.

title: hot cream-style slaw
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat; stir in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard, blending smoothly.
Slowly stir in evaporated milk, then vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring all the time, until mixture thickens.
Add cabbage, onion and green pepper, stirring to mix well.
Continue cooking over medium heat until mixture is heated through, about 2 to 3 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat the milk, margarine, salt, pepper and onion to near boiling.
Transfer this mixture to a large mixing bowl.
Add the cream cheese and potato flakes.
Mix with a mixer until all is blended and potatoes are soupy.
They'll thicken up as they bake. Cover top of potatoes with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Can stay in longer if covered.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato in salt.
Drain.
Mash potato.
Add confectioners sugar, a small amount at a time.
Place mixture on wax paper and roll out.
Spread peanut butter on top and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Roll up and cut into 1-inch rolls.
Slice.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Line baking dish with peaches.
Combine all other ingredients and spread over top of peaches.
Combine 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: In preheated skillet, saute onions in butter until golden brown. Add ground beef and cook until browned, stirring occasionally. Blend in remaining ingredients, except sour cream. Heat until bubbling. Just before serving, add sour cream. Serve over noodles or rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain, pressing out excess liquid.
Set aside. Bake the pie shell for 5 minutes at 425°, then remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Stir together the spinach, cheese and mushrooms; pour into the pie shell.
Blend beaten eggs, cream
and pepper together.
Pour over spinach mixture and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand at least 5 minutes before serving.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add the following ingredients in order: sugar, pecans, self-rising flour, eggs and vanilla.
Stir, do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into large bowl.
In a pan, bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients the margarine, cocoa, water, cinnamon and salt.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Bake in greased 17 1/4 x 11 1/4 x 1-inch sheet pan 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Pour in spaghetti sauce (I use the sauce that has green peppers and mushrooms) and let it come to a boil.
Press crescent rolls into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in ground beef mixture.
Cook at 350° until sides of the rolls turn golden brown.
Take out of oven and sprinkle mozzarella cheese over the top.
Preheat oven on broil and put casserole in until cheese is melted and slightly brown on top.

title: crab or shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in middle of plate. Cover with cocktail sauce.
Serve with onion crackers.

title: christine's pecan squares
directions: For pastry:
Combine 2 cups flour, 1/4 tsp. salt, and 1/2 cup sugar and work in butter with pastry blender or fork.
Mix in vinegar and spread dough in a 10x15x1-inch pan, shape up sides.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour drained asparagus in bottom of dish.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix together mayonnaise, mushrooms, bell pepper and soups.
Layer asparagus, noodles, soup mixture, grated cheese and slivered almonds.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with canned (ready to use) cherry pie filling.
Chill for about 3 hours.

title: easy lemon freeze
directions: In a small saucepan melt butter.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Reserve 1 tablespoon for garnish.
Pat crumbs on bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine pie filling, milk and lemon juice.
Mix well until smooth. Spread into prepared pan.
Top with whipped topping and reserved garnish.
Freeze for 3 hours.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices before serving.

title: large blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease or line muffin tin.
Pam works very well.
Prepare Crunch Topping and set aside.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add 1 tablespoon of the flour to the blueberries, tossing to coat.
In small bowl, combine milk, margarine and eggs until blended.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon evenly into muffin cups.
Sprinkle Crunch Topping over tops.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until pick comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool on wire rack.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook chopped vegetables until tender, about 30 minutes. Press through a
fine sieve. Add spices, tied in a bag, to the pulp and heat
slowly.
Cook
hours or until slightly thick. Remove
spice
bag.
Add
vinegar
and cook to desired thickness. Pour
into
hot
pint
jars,
leaving
inch headspace. Process in a boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: transparent puddings
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, Karo and vanilla; beat slightly.
In double boiler, heat just enough to melt sugar.
Fill shells 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all together; pour into greased tube pan.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Using 9 x 13-inch baking dish, cover bottom with nacho cheese chips.
Layer chicken pieces over chips.
Chop onion and sprinkle over chicken.
Mix together the soups, Ro-Tel, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and onion.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix.
Pour into greased 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp and chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover chicken with water.
Add salt; cook until tender.
Cool and remove skin and bones.
Chop or shred chicken.
Bring water to a boil.
Add shrimp; cook for 3 to 5 minutes, or until shrimp is pink.
Spread broccoli in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine mayonnaise, both soups, lemon juice and pepper; spread 1/3 of mixture over broccoli. Combine chicken and cooked shrimp; spread evenly over casserole. Top with remaining sauce.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine melted butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Sprinkle berries with 1 cup sugar in 9-inch pan.
Cream 1 cup sugar and butter.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to butter mixture.
Pour over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in it with spoon.
Mix pina colada and milk; spoon into holes in cake.
When cake has cooled, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat cake mix, gelatin, water and oil at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each. Add 3/4 of strawberries and juice, reserving remainder for icing. Mix well. Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) round cake pans lined with wax paper or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and spread with icing.

title: judith c. michael's strip dumplings
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough (stiff enough to roll).
Roll out and cut into 3/4-inch wide strips.
Cut strips 3 to 4-inches long.
Drop into hot broth and cook slowly, about 10 minutes.

title: tuna and cucumber sandwiches
directions: Drain water from cans.
Mix tuna, mayonnaise and onion together in a bowl.
Use more mayonnaise if a richer, juicier mix is desired.
Add seasoning to taste:
a few good shakes of each should suffice.
Spread mixture on your favorite bread.
Add cucumber slices.
If a cooler mixture is desired, prepare the night before and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Vary spices according to taste.
4 servings.

title: kibbi bis sayniyyi(baked kibbi)
directions: Cover burghul with cold water; soak for 10 minutes.
Drain and press between palms of hand to remove excess water.
Mix onion and spices together with fingers.
Knead meat and spices thoroughly; add crushed wheat and continue kneading.
Dip hands in ice and water while kneading in order to soften kibbi.
Run the kneaded mixture through a meat grinder two to three times.

title: crumb-coated chicken
directions: In small bowl
beat together eggs, butter and salt.
In shallow dish place crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in egg, butter and salt mixture, then coat with cornflake crumbs and cheese mixture.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish with meatiest
pieces to outside edges of dish.
When all pieces have been coated, cover dish with wax paper.
Microwave at High for 22
to 25 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes.

title: million dollar pie(2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pan and bake according to directions (until just brown).
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, Miracle Whip, garlic powder and dill weed and spread over crescent crust. Top with veggies, cheese and sausage (optional).

title: ultimate cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cheese with ingredients.
Roll into a ball. Garnish with parsley or roll in chopped parsley.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix and cool sugar and hot water; add orange juice with 3 cans water,
pineapple,	bananas,
mixed fruit and cherries. Freeze. Stir once
or
twice
during
freezing.
When thawing only thaw to the point
mixture	is like slush.	Delicious and refreshing in hot summer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits and nuts well. Add whipped cream. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Serve in dessert dish with a spoon of whipped cream on top.

title: sausage pie
directions: Place sausage in a baking pan.
Brown at 350° for 15 minutes; set aside.
In a skillet, saute peppers in oil for 3 minutes. Place in 3-quart casserole.
Add the sausage and the next 7 ingredients.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cotton pickin good cake
directions: Mix in a large mixing bowl on low speed for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour
three
9-inch
pans.
Pour into pans and bake. Cool completely, then frost.

title: pepparkakor(swedish gingersnaps)
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, butter, eggs and molasses together. Sift together dry ingredients and stir into sugar mixture.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter at medium speed.
Slowly add milk.
Fold topping into mixture.
Turn into pie shell and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm.
To serve, remove pie from freezer half hour before serving.
